Commentary: On a length, outside off, pushed towards point.
On a length, around off, nipping back in, Sharma looks to tuck but misses and is hit on the pads.
The leg cutter perhaps, short of a good length, but a bit too straight. RS looks to tuck it away but misses and wears it on the pads again.
Broad goes for the length delivery again, but outside off, Sharma comes ahead and strokes this one to the fielder stationed at covers.
Goes more further up this time. Bowls a very full ball on the off pole, Rohit is not fazed by this as he gets his bat down in time to block.
A good first testing over by Broad comes to an end. A maiden too. On a length, outside off, Rohit shoulders arms this time.
Short of a length to start. Outside off, pushed to the off side.
Short again, excellent pace, pushed to the off side, with a little bit of a bottom edge.

OUT! LBW! That is as dead as a stone by Stone! Massive misjudgement by Gill. This is on a length, outside off and Shubman shoulders arms. To his dismay, the ball comes back in a long way and hits him on the pads. SG knows he is in danger, the moment he is hit. He looks at the umpire, who takes little time in raising his finger. Gill slowly walks towards Rohit, hoping that there would be something that will make his partner tell him to take the review. Nothing. Impact does not matter, as he was not offering a shot. He was hit below the knee roll, so height would have been umpire's call at the most. In fact, Ball Tracker shows it to be hitting off stump. Wobbly seam doing the trick, with the inner half of the seam hitting the batsman. Too close to the off stump to be left. Perhaps, Shubman left it on length, but given this is India, it is risky.
Another good length delivery around off, Pujara gets his bat down well to defend this one out towards mid on.
Good length and on middle, Pujara clips this one to mid-wicket. 'WAIT, WAIT', says Pujara, to Rohit, regarding the single.
A wonderful over by Stone. Gets a wicket maiden right on his first over of this Test. In the channel outside off, Pujara has on interest in playing at this one. India yet to open their account.

FOUR! BRILLIANT! That will calm the nerves of the Indian fans. A half volley, wide outside off, Rohit leans and drives it through the covers. Broad did not give him anything to drive in the opening over and the moment he got an opportunity here, Sharma pounced.
On a length, around middle, helped towards square leg for a single.
Outside off, on a length, watchfully pushed away.
On a good length and on middle, Pujara works this one to mid-wicket. Is loud and quick to deny the single too.
Another length ball around the off pole, Pujara is solid in his defense again, as this is pushed towards mid on.

EDGY FOUR! Boundary to start and boundary to end the over. Not how Pujara would have wanted to play at this one but it does not matter as it has worked out in his favor. On a length, outside off, Pujara looks to play this one with soft hands but the ball takes the outside edge and goes through the slip region andÂ into the third man fence. 9 runs off the over. Replays later show that Stokes got his fingertips to this one at second slip but failed to stop it in spite of a dive to his right.

Lovely shot, good stop. Full and outside off, Rohit drives it straight back. Stone gets down to make a half stop and takes some pace off the shot. Moeen Ali get across from extra cover and keeps the batsmen to a single. The stand moves to 10 from 10 balls.
Fullish ball outside off, Pujara prods and then leaves it alone.
Full, outside off, watchfully defended.
Bowls a shorter one outside off, Pujara sways away from the line and lets this one be.
Length, around off, CP pushes this one to mid on. A loud and clear 'NAHI' is heard from Pujji.
Well left by Pujara. Stone bowls this one a length, outside off, Pujara leaves it alone. Another good over by Olly.
On a length, outside off, solidly defended.
Fullish, a touch wide outside off, Rohit leans and pushes this well away from his body through the region between cover and point. Two runs taken.
Landed on a length, outside off, Sharma walks into the shot and defends it back down the track.

Ohhh...good bowling again. Bowls this one on a length and outside off, Sharma was in two minds on whether to play it or leave it. Decides to hang his bat in the air and the ball takes the inside edge and bounces back to the keeper.
FOUR! Supreme shot. Elegance on display from Rohit. On a length, outside off, Sharma just pushes this one firmly through the mid off region and into the ropes downtown.
Outside off, length, left alone.
On a length, around off, moving away slightly, Pujara defends it watchfully.
Fuller and wider outside off, the tempter to drive, the master of patience shows no interest.

Nice try. Stone goes for the short ball, outside off and gets it to nip back in. Cheteshwar looks to work it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the body. There is a leg gully in place as well. Chepu sets off for a single but is sent back. There was never a single.
It is fuller. Or just a tad short of full. On off, Pujara watchfully blocks this one out towards the cover region.
Slightly behind the good length and outside the off pole, Pujara will leave these type of deliveries all day long.
Another really good over by Olly comes to an end. His second maiden. Back of a length and around off, CP works this one to the square leg region.
Full, outside off, nicely pushed, well into the gap, to the right of extra cover and the left of mid off. A single is taken.
On a length, around off, coming in, worked to the left of leg gully, all along the ground, for a run to fine leg.
Outside off, blocked towards cover. Thoughts about the single, but well aborted quickly.

A loud, loud appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Broad bowls a good length delivery on middle, Rohit looks to tuck this one away to the leg side but it seems that it has taken the inside edge of the bat and then rapped him on the pads. Broad is very interested in the review but captain Root opts not to go for it. A good decision.
On off, good length, pushed to the off side.

FOUR! That was in the air for some time but the Indian fans can breathe easy as the ball goes over the fielder and into the ropes. What was that? Good length and around off, Rohit looks to play this straight. But the ball lands and then generates a massive puff of dust. This causes the ball to shoot up, making Rohit to lose control on his shot. He ends up chipping itÂ towards the mid on region but luckily for him, it is over the man there. Takes a couple of bounces and into the ropes at long on. A good end to the over for the Indians. This is just the 7th over on Day 1! Are we even going to see a Day 4?
On a length, outside off, lifts sharply, Pujara feels for it. The ball seams away and then beats the outside edge.
Around middle, worked to the leg side for a single.
Sliding on the pads of Rohit there, Sharma clips it towards deep mid-wicket and gets a brace.

FOUR! Hit very hard and another boundary for Rohit. Any sort of width offered to him and he will pounce. On a shorter length outside off, Sharma slaps this one through point but the ball takes the toe end of the bat and flies to the right of gully, to the backward point fence.
Fuller, on off, Sharma digs this one out.

Slightly behind the good length and on off, the ball stops on him again as it hits the turf and comes to him. Rohit was looking to push this one away but the ball takes the inner half of the blade and goes to the mid on region.
Massive explosion on the very first ball.Â Full and outside off, Pujara leans and then pushes it with the away turn, through the off side, for a single. The stand moves to 30 from 40 balls.
Full, around middle, softly nudged towards square leg.

Ohh... we have a review! Landed around leg, Rohit went for the paddle but missed and was hit on the pads. There was a shout for leg before, but the umpire shook his head. Root was interested but Leach seemed to be indicating that it was going down the leg side. Root had a chat with his keeper and then, at the last moment, went for the review. Ball Tracker shows it to be pitching on leg stump but as Leach indicated, going down leg. Impact itself was outside leg and England have lost a review.
Floated and on off and middle, eased down towards long off for aÂ single.
Flat, on off, Pujara stays back and blocks it out.
Now comes on his front foot to this full ball on off and shows off his defensive push. A good start by Leach.

FOUR! CARESSED! Rohit has always had the gift of timing, hasn't he? Overpitched, outside off, Sharma leans and drives it in front of point. The ball races away. That is his 5th boundary of the innings, on a pitch which has no pace whatsoever.
Outside off, on a length, dabbed towards gully.
Fuller, outside off, driven towards cover.
Straighter this time and on the pads, helped towards square leg for a single. ChePu wanted the double but Moeen Ali did well to run in and collect the ball and stop the batters just to the single.
Outside off, length, tapped to point.
Length, closer to the off pole, but not close enough for Pujara to try and block. Leaves it alone.
Full, around leg, pushed towards - WHAT? A long off already? An easy single then. Rohit moves to 30 from 32 balls.
Very keen to use his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball and nurdles it to short mid-wicket.
Shorter length is the effect. Just what Pujara wants. Rocks back in a flash and cuts, but finds point.
Full and loopy on middle, kept out well by Pujara.
Pujara comes forward again to a full ball and looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and hits the pads, to then roll to the off side.
Flighted and on off, Pujara blocks this one to the on side. Just the solitary run of the over.

On a length, outside off, pushed towards cover. So far, no reverse swing on offer. It was seen pretty early in the first Test. Given the abrasive look of this deck, doesn't seem long before we start seeing the ball to reverse.

SIX! Goes after this one. Cannot say he hit that from the middle of the bat, but he gets the desired result. Short, around off, Rohit immediately goes for the pull. He does not connect cleanly, in fact it is a bit of a top edge too. There is a deep square leg in place as well, but the ball is well wide of him. Clears the ropes but the umpire wants a cross check. Sends it upstairs and the replay shows that the ball tipped over.

FOUR! This one is from the middle of the bat. All along the ground as well. Short and outside off again, Sharma goes for the pull once more and rolls his wrists over that shot. Gets it towards backward square leg, splitting fine leg and deep mid-wicket. Has rocketed to 40 from 35 balls.
Good length and on middle and leg from Ben, it is helped towards fine leg for one. Sharma ran the first one hard but could not turn this into a double.
Pujara is in no sort of hurry as he pushes thisÂ good length ball on off gently towards the man present at mid on.
A dot to end. Length, on off, tapped to the off side. 11 runs off the over. A big one for India.
Full, around middle, Rohit stays leg side of the ball and drives it towards cover.
Full, around off, watchfully defended.
Full, around off again, massive puff of dust emanates but it is watchfully defended. If there is a Tuesday or a Wednesday in this game, cannot imagine what it will be like, trying to bat.

EDGED, DID THAT CARRY? No. Nervous moment for Rohit. He lunges to defend this pitched up ball outside off but it shoots up and takes the top half of the bat. Lobs towards first slip where Ben Stokes dives, but is not able to hold in. In fact, the replay shows that it dropped just in front of him.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, pushed carefully to the off side.
Comes down the track, takes it on the full and hammers it straight back. Moeen gets a hand to it and deflects it towards mid on.
Uses his feet again, gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it through the covers for a single.
Full, around off, worked with a closed bat face towards short mid-wicket.

Loopy and around off, Sharma comes ahead slightly and strokes this one through mid on for a single. Also brings up the 50-run stand between these two and also brings up the 50 for India. A good one for India so far but these two will have to go on.
Comes to the pitch of the full ball on off and blocks.
A single to end. Tosses it up and lands it around off, Pujara eases this one through mid on. 3 off Moeen's first over.
Steps out and drives this wide of mid off for a single.

FOUR! Well, that needed a good connection and Rohit gets it. Pretty full and straight. Risky to sweep. If missed, then LBW or timber. But Sharma had made up his mind pretty early. Lunged, went for the sweep and dismissed it through mid-wicket.
Fuller, around off, watchfully defended.

FIFTY FOR ROHIT SHARMA! Also, brings it up with a four. There is applause all around with the crowd cheering him on. Gets it off just 47 balls and he has been really good for India today. Did not quite play this well in the first Test but you can never count him out. The Indian dressing room too is clapping and Rohit acknowledges everyone by raising his blade. A full toss on off and middle, Sharma gets on his knees and sweeps this one hard to the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, RS blocks to the on side.
Landed outside off, Pujara goes back and dabs it to the off side.
FOUR! Quality shot. Comes down the track and flicks it past short leg. Beats square leg and the ball races to the fence.

Comes down the track again, but this time, is not quite to the pitch of the ball to defend. Gets hit on the pads and Moeen appeals for LBW but Pujara was way too far down the track. The ball lobs to first slip where Ben Stokes collects and appeals for the catch as well, but no wood involved.
Flighted on off, Pujara comes down the track and looks to block but is only able to pad this one away.
Floated and on middle, worked to the leg side.
Comes down the track and clips this one to mid-wicket to see off the over.
Full and around off, Pujara comes down the track and drives it uppishly, back to the bowler. Does not carry.
Comes down again and this time, solidly defends.

Massive, massive shout for LBW. Turned down. Jack Leach though, reckons that it was going over the top. Rohit had come down the track to defend but missed, getting hit on the pads. Hmmm... Ball Tracker shows the impact to be umpire's call, more than 3 metres but then, bouncing over the top. Good call from Leach not to take the review.
Full and flighted on the pads, Rohit gets on his knees and paddles this one uppishly over the short fine leg region. Gets a single by the time Moeen can run to his right and collect the ball.
Goes on the back foot and defends this one out.

Well played by Pujara but Burns does exceptionally well to pull this one before the ropes. He got rid of the ball before he hauls himself over the advertisement triangles. Fractionally short and outside off, Pujara goes on his back foot and slashes this one through point. Two fielders give it chase and it looks like the ball will win the race. Burns does not give up and does well to pull it back. The umpire refers it upstairs to check whether it is a boundary and the replay confirms it is a clean save. Two runs taken.

EDGED, BUT SHORT! Shorter, outside off, spinning in slightly, Rohit stays back to defend. The ball takes the outside edge but does not carry to first slip. Ben Stokes is not able to stop it cleanly as he falls, trying to stop the ball. Deflects it behind. Ben Foakes himself has to run back to collect the ball and the batsmen pinch a single.
Comes down the track and whips it with the angle through mid-wicket for a couple. The stand moves to 70 from 95 balls.
Outside off, blocked to the off side.
Pujara does what he does so well against spinners, coming down the track. He does so again and clips this to mid-wicket for a quick run.
Comes on the front foot and blocks this one out, does Rohit.

FOUR! Another boundary for Rohit and India going along nicely now. After their early blow, this is what was needed. Shorter, outside off, Sharma slaps this one through the backward point region and the timing on this will ensure that the ball and the ropes meet again.
Tossed up, outside off, Pujara comes down the track and drives it to mid off. The fielder is pretty deep but Pujara declines the single. There was one on offer.
Takes it this time. Pushes this through the covers and takes the single. Moves to 20.

Excellent bowling. Challenging line from Leach. And length too. This is neither full, nor short. Nor is it flighted much. So Rohit is tentative as he looks to defend, coming half forward. Gets an inside edge, which hits the pads and rolls towards fine leg. A run taken.
Flighted, outside off, Pujara gets his pad ahead but does not offer any shot to this one. Foakes collects.
On middle, blocked to the on side.
Slightly short and on the pads, clipped to the short fine leg region. Pujara comes down the track and looks for the run but Rohit declines it and ChePu takes a turn and heads back into his crease.
Full, around off, worked wide of mid on for a single.
Comes down the track, is not able to get to the pitch of the ball and then pads it to the off side.
Full, around off, Pujara comes down the track again, is not quite to the pitch of the ball and pushes it to the off side.
Uses his feet quickly again and works this to the long on region for one.

FOUR! Excellent placement from Rohit and he moves to 62 now, off just 59 balls. Slightly short and outside off, Sharma does not have to do too much, just opens up the face of his bat and guides this one to the deep backward point region for yet another boundary.
Looks like Sharma is looking at Pujara and picking up a few things. This time, he uses his feet well to get to the pitch of the ball and helps this through mid on for a single.
Full, around middle, Rohit comes down the track and drives it to long off for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIP! Leach has persisted and eventually, been rewarded. Full, just outside off, Pujara does nothing much wrong. Pushes at it with firm hands. The ball hits the deck, generates a massive puff of dust and takes the outside edge. Sharp chance for Ben Stokes at first slip who takes it nicely to his left. The stand of 85 has been broken. Looked like Pujara wanted to use his feet but then, indecision cost him.

Brave leave! Almost a replica of the Steve O'Keefe moment in 2017. Landed outside off, Kohli lunges and then let it be. But the ball does not spin away. It goes straight on and just misses the off stump!
Full and floated on middle, Kohli comes forward and gets his bat ahead to block this one out.
Similar sort of delivery to the last ball. Virat again prods forward and defends to the off side.

Tosses it up and lands it just around the off pole, Kohli pushes this one to the mid on region. Looks like the crowd will have to wait some more to see Kohli open his account now. Massive cheers all around, though.
Full, around off, pushed towards long on for a single.

OUT! BOWLED! Moeen has dismissed Kohli! One wicket brings another and the Chepauk is in a hush. Beautiful bowling and Ashwin will already be licking his lips. Full, outside off, the Indian skipper leans to drive. But the ball drifts in beautifully, spins in a mile, goes past the inside edge and hits the stumps! Kohli hears the death rattle but does not want to go. He asks Rohit whether he is bowled because he feels that the bails have been dislodged off the keeper's gloves. The umpire now takes it upstairs but the first replay shows that the ball has hit the stumps. A duck for Super V!
FOUR! Nice gift to a new man. A full toss, outside off, Rahane steps out, gets to the ball and drives it to the left of cover.
Flighted and around off, Rahane blocks this one to the off side. Chants of 'INDIA, INDIAAAA' rolling around the ground now.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Full and loopy on middle, Rahane keeps this one out. A great over for England and Moeen. They get the big fish - Super V!
Floated, around middle, pushed towards mid on.
Comes down the track, drives it through cover but Joe Root gets across to his right and stops it brilliantly on the move, with his right hand.
Around off, pushed to the off side.
Full and loopy on off, Sharma blocks it out.
Flighted and on leg, Rohit clips this one to the right of mid on for a quick single.
The arm ball this time from Leach and he bowls this on the middle pole, Rahane goes back on his back foot and gets his bat across to fend this one out.
Full, outside off, watchfully pushed towards backward point.

FOUR! THRASH! At the moment, Rohit Sharma is on a different planet. Outside off, Rohit gets down and sweeps it powerfully through mid-wicket. There are two men in the deep on the leg side. One at deep backward square leg and the other at deep mid-wicket, a bit squarer and three quarters in front of the ropes. Sharma bisects them to perfection. He has moved to 70 from just 68 balls and is dictating terms.
Full, outside off, driven wide of long off for a single. The stand moves to 10 from 13 balls.
Tossed up and on middle, whipped to the mid-wicket region.
Outside off, full, Rahane gets ahead and pads it away to the point region.
Tossed up again and outside the off pole, Ajinkya prods forward and defends it.
Landed outside off, sharp away turn, left alone.
Comes down the track this time and blocks it solidly.
FOUR! CLASSY! What a shot. Full, around middle, Rohit comes forward and just punches it against the spin. The ball races to Leach's right and beats mid on to his left. 100 UP FOR INDIA.
On off, blocked to the off side. Rohit thought of taking the single but Rahane sends him back.
On middle, keeps this one out solidly, does RS.
Loopy and outside off, Rohit senses no danger in leaving this one alone and do so too.

JUST WIDE! The plan of having a leg gully very nearly works. A length ball, around off, Rahane gets across and looks to nudge it fine. But he cannot keep it down. It goes uppishly, towards backward square leg. Ollie Pope at leg gully, dives full stretch to his right but cannot get there. A single taken.

EDGED, FOUR! Good length again. Just short of full, outside off, Rohit is forced to play at it. But there is a bit of late movement, which squares him up. Gets an outside edge but it goes to ground. It is in between second slip and gully, racing to the third man fence.
Short and outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single. Moves to 80 from 78 balls and the stand is worth 20 from just 25 deliveries.
Slightly behind the good length and on off, Jinks plays this one back to Stone. 'NOOOOO', a loud and clear call by Rahane, for the run.
Another length ball, on off, Rahane looks to block but the ball tails back in and takes the inside edge and hits the body, to roll to the off side.
Rahane does well to avoid this one. A very quick ball by Olly. He fires in a short ball on middle, Rahane sways away from the line and lets it through to Foakes. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Flighted and around off, Rohit prods forward and blocks it out solidly.
Full and outside off, Sharma offers no shot to this one.
Identical to the last delivery as Sharma thinks about playing at this one but does not do so, in the end. Foakes collects and whips the bails off but Rohit's foot was in the crease.
Loopy and on off, Sharma looks to block but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes towards point.
Well left by RS. Flighted and outside the off pole, Sharma again offers no shot.
Driven but straight to the fielder. Full and floated on off, Sharma drives but only finds the cover fielder. Does not go for the run this time. A maiden to start off the first over post Lunch.
On a good length and outside off, Rahane drives this one straight to the mid off region.

Excellent stop by the skipper, Joe Root. Stone bowls this one on a length and on middle, Ajinkya flicks this one to the left of Root at leg gully and he dives to that side and stops it well. Good work and the others will look at their leader and look to follow the same.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

EDGY COUPLE. A good length ball on the off pole, Rahane looks to flick this one to the leg side but the ball takes the leading edge and goes over the cover region but not to any fielder. The batters collect two runs.
Jinks pushes this one to the fielder present at mid off.
Short of a length and outside off, Ajinkya looks to slash this one away but the ball takes the inside edge and rolls to the off side.
Tossed up and around off, Sharma blocks.

An appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. Full and flighted on off and middle, Rohit leans forward looking to block this one outÂ but the ball takes the bat first and then the pad and so the umpire does not think this will be out.

Another appeal for lbw but again, the umpire shakes his head. Full and flighted on off, Sharma looks to get on his knees and looks to paddle sweep this one away but he misses and gets hit on the pads. Leach is loud in his enquiry but the umpire says no. Once again, Root does not opt for the review.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

Two this time. Loopy and around off, Sharma skips down the track and lofts this one over the cover region and by the time the fielder can clean up in the deep, Rohit comes back for the second. Moves onto 82 now.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, length, Jinks lets it be.
Good length and on off and middle, nips back in after hitting the deck as Ajinkya looks to flick this away but misses. Takes the pad and goes to the leg gully fielder.
Back of a length and on off, Rahane swivels and pulls this one towards fine leg for a single.
Short of a length, on the off pole, Rohit shows the full face of the blade and defends it back solidly.
Good length on off, pushed to mid on this time by RS.

SLASH AND A MISS! Ohh..good ball to finish the over. Stone goes for a short of a length ball outside off, tempting Rohit to cut this one away and Sharma looks to flirt with this one too. He does not make any connection and the ball goes towards Foakes.
Full, around off, nice loop, Rahane lunges to defend.
Down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter, around off, pushed to the off side.
Looped up nicely, outside off, driven straight to short extra cover.
The arm ball now, very quick, Rohit has a good stride to block.
Comes down the track now, pushes it to the left of the bowler, beats short extra cover to his right but there is mid off in place.
A short ball, extra bit of bounce, outside off, Rahane counters it nicely, keeping it down towards the leg side.

FOUR! Sounded good, is good. Frustration for Stone and Root. The field is set for the fuller delivery, but Stone bowls it short. It is quick, 144 ks, but on a slow deck, it is pristine gold for a batsman. Outside off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce, is deep in the crease and punches it through the covers. Moves to 13 in a stand of 30.
Outside off, pushed towards point.

FOUR! CRISP! That is the kind of Ajinkya Rahane the crowd has come to see. Nice, decisive footwork. No half thoughts. A length ball, outside off, Rahane gets a good stride forward and punches it on the up, wide of mid off and to the right of extra cover.
Landed outside off, short and at pace, pushed towards point.
Yorker length, outside off, pretty full it turns out to be, played towards point.
Looped up, outside off, driven back to the bowler.
Comes down the track, drives it towards long on but short mid-wicket intercepts with a dive to his left.
Loops up, outside off, very less pace. Rohit leans and pushes it towards cover.
Opens the face of the bat now and eases it through the covers for a single.
Quicker delivery, short in length, extra bit of bounce, pushed awkwardly towards cover.
The arm ball to end the over, Jinx stays back to defend.
Full, around off, Rohit lunges and works it to the leg side.
Lunges again to smother another ball.
Tossed up, around off, pushed down to long on for a single.
Oohh.... that was in the air... Full, around off, Rahane comes forward and looks to flick. It goes off the inner half though, just wide of short leg, to his left. A single taken.
On middle and off, pushed down the track.

FOUR! THUMP! First shot of anger in this session. Full and outside off, Rohit gets down and mows a slog sweep over mid-wicket. Deep square leg races to his left but cannot get there. The stand moves to 41 now.
Tossed up, around middle, pushed towards mid on.
The quicker arm ball, on off, Rahane goes back and pushes it towards point.

What an absolute peach from Jack Leach. Plenty of revolutions, tossing it up, landing it outside off, short of full, generating a puff of dust, getting the batsman forward and then getting it to rip past the outside edge. Good take by Ben Foakes as well.
This one goes straight through, does not turn, defended watchfully.
Around middle, whipped through mid-wicket for a single.
Full, around middle, well blocked out.
Full, around off, Rahane looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
On middle, pushed back down the track.
Quicker through the air, Jinx goes back to defend.
Full, outside off, AR gets down and sweeps this ferociously through backward square leg. Jack Leach stops it there, at the ropes. A single taken. Rahane moves to 20 now.
Jumps down the track and pushes it towards long on for a run.
Full, outside off, Rahane lunges and keeps it well out of reach of short leg.
Landed outside off, goesÂ straight through, Rohit shoulders arms.
Comes straight down the track now, works it wide of mid on and gets a single, as the fielder races to his right to dive and stop the ball. Into the 90s, moves Mr. Sharma.
Full, around off, watchfully pushed towards the off side.
The arm ball, around off, Rahane shoulders arms this time.
Short and around off, Jinx goes back and works it through mid-wicket for a run.
Around off, worked through mid-wicket for one more.
Looped up, around off, worked straight to short mid-wicket.
Comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Again, Rohit comes down the track and looks to workÂ it through mid on but Rory Burns gets across to his left from short mid-wicket.
This one drifts in, from outside off, Sharma lunges to block but the ball spins in as well, takes the inside edge and lobs in the air. Lands quickly as well, before short leg can get across.

SIX! THUNDEROUS! Brilliant hit. Rohit realizes that defending is not going to keep batsmen safe on thisÂ pitch, with explosions seen already. Jumps out, gets to the pitch of the ball and smashes the bones out of it, over long off. Mid off was up but it would not have mattered anyway. Moves to 97 now. 50-STAND IS UP AS WELL.
Full, around off, 'Ro' watchfully defends.
On a length, around off, pushed to the off side.
Back of a length, around off, defended down the track.
Fuller now, around off, Rahane is watchfully solid in blocking.
EDGY BUT FOUR! Full, outside off, moving away, Rahane looks to drive, pushing away from hisÂ body. It is a leg cutter and the ball goes off the outer half of the bat, behind backward point.

Very full, around off, driven towards well - a silly mid on in place. It is Joe Root himself, who is standing right in front of Rohit Sharma at the non-striker's end. Fields and then has a shy at the striker's end, showing needless aggression. Rahane was going nowhere. Gets the crowd going though.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Full, around off, flicked straight to short leg.

Ahh.... nearly. Moeen tosses this up and Rohit comes down the track to get to his century with a big hit. But the ball dips on him, comes on late and then spins in from outside off. Goes off the inner half of the bat, towards short mid-wicket.

Oh dear, what was that? Full, outside off, Sharma gets down and across, looks for a paddle but the ball hits the toe end of the bat. It lobs in the air but does not carry to Rory Burns running in from short mid-wicket. For all his hard work to get here, don't want to throw it away, do you?
Outside off, this time RS watchfully pushes it towards cover, invoking applause from the crowd.
A full toss now, Ro hits it straight back to the bowler.
Jumps down the track and works it wide of long on for a single. Moves to 98.
On a length, around off, watchfully defended.
Hmmmm.... just a few nervous moments in the 90s. Outside off, Rohit looks to steer it to third man, but sans moving his feet. Is beaten.
Back of a length, around off, Ro pushes it back to the bowler.
This one skids through, just stays a touch low, RS gets his bat down in time to work it to short mid-wicket.
A bit of miscommunication now. Full, outside off, Rohit pushes it towards cover, sets off for a single but then changes his mind.
Around off, solidly and watchfully defended.
Tossed up, outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Gets down and employs the sweep shot, for a single to fine leg.

100 IN 130 BALLS! The Chepauk is on its feet. What a knock from Rohit Sharma. Single-handedly dismantling the opposition on a pitch where his partners have struggled. Gets there with a lap towards fine leg and runs hard for the second. His 7th century in Tests. Rohit has scored 100 out of India's 148, which is nearly 65 percent! Now, for a daddy hundred.
Bunts this down to long on for a run.
Full, outside off, driven straight to cover.
Comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, around off, pushed towards cover.
A bit too straight, worked through mid on for a couple. 150 UP FOR INDIA. 286 balls left in the day. With Pant yet to come, 300 is on the cards tonight itself.
Outside off, solidly defended.
Around off, moving away slightly, pushed to the off side.
This time, he gets that shot away. Waits for the ball to arrive and steers it behind gully, for a couple.
Leg cutter to end the over, outside off, let go of.
Short outside off, Rahane pushes it wide of mid off, to his left. He sets off for a single but Rohit is a bit unsure. 'AAJA, AAJA, AAJA!' is the call and eventually, they make it through.
Around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Comes down the track now and bunts it towards short mid-wicket again.
Shorter, around off, punched back to the bowler.
Nicely played, beautifully placed. Rohit comes down the track and whips it past a diving Rory Burns at short mid-wicket for another couple.
Outside off, dabbed towards backward point for a single. The stand is worth 70 now.
On a good length and on off, Sharma pushes this one to the mid on region.
Another good length ball and on middle, whipped to the right of mid on again.
A single now as this good length ball around off is tapped towards covers by Rohit.
Length, on off, Rahane offers a dead bat in defense.
On a length, on the off pole, Ajinkya pushes this one to covers.
Fuller and on the middle pole, Rahane whips this one to the fielder at mid-wicket. 'No' is the call for the single.
Comes on the front foot and defends this one with a straight bat.
Does what he did on the last ball again, does Rohit. Blocks to the off side.
Loopy and around off, Sharma looks to block this one but the ball spins away and takes the outer half of the blade and goes to the point region.

Ohh...EDGY! So close. Leach providing Rohit with some problems. Short and on middle, Sharma looks to get his bat close to his body and guide this one to the off side but the ball takes the inside edge and goes through short fine leg and Burns does well to chase and pull it back, before the ropes. Three runs.
FOUR! Classy shot from Rahane. Moves to 31 now. Short, outside off, Rahane waits and waits and waits and then at the right time, he slashes this one through the backward point region for a boundary.
On off, pushed to covers now.
Full and loopy on off, Sharma whips this one through mid-wicket for one. Stand moves to 79 of 149 balls now.
On middle, Rahane clips this one to the leg side.
Nice loop, full, on off, blocked out by Jinks.

IN THE AIR...SAFE! Rahane looks for the big one and plays this one uppish but it falls just short of the fielder at mid on. Loopy on off, Rahane looks to slam this one over mid on but does not time it well. Plays it on the up but short of the man there.
Short, around off, Rahane goes on the back foot and punches this one through covers. The batters complete three runs.
On middle, Rohit works it to the on side for a single.
Full and flighted on leg, Sharma works this one through mid on for a single.
Identical to the last ball, Rahane nudges this one to the square leg region for a quick run.
Rohit blocks this one towards the silly point fielder.

Another full ball, nicely looped up as well, on middle and leg, Sharma whips this one nicely through the mid-wicket region. Broad is giving it chase and it looks like the ball will win the race. Stuart, though does not give up and pulls it back nicely before the ropes. Three runs. They want to check if this is a clean save and replays show that it is. Great stuff from the veteran.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
On off, played towards covers for one run.
Full toss on middle, whipped to the short mid-wicket fielder.
On off, blocked.
Comes on the front foot and blocks this time.

FOUR! Exceptional batting from Rohit Sharma. Bags another boundary and he is on the move. Flighted and on off, Sharma goes on his knees and mows a slog sweep over square leg and the ball finds the ropes.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Rohit works this one through mid-wicket and the fielder at long on runs to his right and stops it. Will not stop the batters from taking the single though.
Short, on off, punched to deep covers and the batters rotate the strike.
Flat again, on off, Ajinkya cuts this one but finds the fielder at point.
Goes on the back foot and blocks this one to silly point.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Full and floated on off, Rahane drives this one to the cover region.
Tosses it up and lands it around off, Rahane blocks to silly point again. Just 1 off the over.
Full and loopy on middle, whipped to mid-wicket.
Stays back and flicks this one to mid-wicket again.

FOUR! It was in the air but just away from Ben Stokes at first slip. Shortish and around off, Rahane leans back and then cuts this one late uppish, just past Stokes and the ball trickles through to the ropes at third man. Replays later show that Ben did well to anticipate that Rahane would cut it and as soon as he saw Rahane moves to his back foot, he started moving to his right,Â anticipating that stroke. Good match awareness by Stokes.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Rohit shows off his front foot defense on this occasion.
On middle, clipped through mid-wicket for one. This stand now moved to 99. A very good one for India.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

100 RUN STAND IS UP. Brilliant batting by these two and they want to further this number even more. Flat, on off, punched to deep covers and Moeen chases and pulls it back before the ropes. The batters get a couple.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Floated, outside off, spins away and Rohit dabs this one late towards the point region.
RS punches this one to the mid off region this time.
Full, loopy, outside off, left alone.
On a good length and around off, 138ks, Rahane keeps it out.
Similar to the previous delivery and Ajinkya offers a dead bat in defense.
Pushed to the cover region this time.
On a good length, outside off, stays a touch low as well this time, Rahane looks to push this one away but he fails to connect his blade with the leather.
Length, around off, Rahane pushes it back to Olly.
Short of a length and around off, Rahane taps this one towards the point region.
Flighted on off, Rohit keeps it out.
Ro blocks this one towards silly point.
Full and tossed up and on leg, Sharma tucks this one to square leg for a single.
Full and flighted on off, Ajinkya pushes this one to point.

EDGY AND SHORT OF ROOT! So close. Flighted and on off, spins away from the right-hander as he looked to block. It takes the glove and goes to the right of Root at the second slip position. Root does dive to that side but it falls well before him.
Short, on off, punched to covers for a single. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Rahane looks to push but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Full delivery on middle, Rahane pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length on off, Rahane pushes it to point.
Full delivery on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.

Floated delivery on off, Sharma looks to sweep but gets hit on the arm.
On off, Sharma defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Sharma flicks it to short leg.
Tossed up ball on off, Sharma looks to sweep but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire denies it.

Short of a length delivery on middle, Rahane looks to pull but gets it off the gloves. It lands safely towards fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.

Good length delivery outside off, Sharma offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on off, Sharma keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Rohit offers a solid defense on this one.

FOUR! Nicely played! Full delivery on off, Rahane comes down the track and drives it through covers for a boundary.

FOUR! Cracking shot! Short ball on off, Rahane makes room and cuts it hard through point for a boundary.

FOUR! That is put away! Short delivery on middle, Rahane pulls it through square leg for a boundary. He moves to 49 with that!
Back of a length on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Rahane looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire denies it.
Full toss on middle, Sharma drives it through mid on for a single.
Floated delivery on off, Rahane blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket.

BEATEN! Short delivery on off, Rahane looks to cut but misses it due to the turn on this one. It goes safely towards the keeper.
50 for Ajinkya Rahane! It has been a good innings from him! Full delivery on middle, Rahane pushes it towards mid on for a quick single.
Good length delivery on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Full and outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to this alone.

Loopy delivery on off, Rahane sweeps it through mid-wicket for a run.

Tossed up delivery on off, Rahane looks to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR! Bess makes a mess of it in the deep and it will be a boundary. Not his fault entirely though as Bess' foot got caught on the turf and that is why the misfield occurred. Nicely swept though from Rohit! Floated delivery on middle, Sharma sweeps it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Loopy delivery on off, Rohit guides it towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get two runs.
On middle, Sharma plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg for a single.
Short ball on off, Rahane punches it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
On off, Rahane defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma looks to defend but gets it off the inner half of the bat. It goes towards square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Good length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Rahane drives it towards mid off for a quick single.
Length delivery on middle, Sharma flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Rahane blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length on off, Rahane keeps it out.
BEATEN! Googly outside off, Sharma looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
Floated delivery on middle, Sharma defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Sharma flicks it to mid-wicket.
On off, Rohit defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma pushes it back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Sharma looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The skipper starts off with a maiden over.
Good length delivery on middle, Rahane blocks it off the front foot towards square leg. Jinks thinks about the single but opts not to, in the end.
Length delivery on off, Rahane offers a solid defense on this one.
Back of a length on off, Rahane pushes it to covers.
Short delivery on middle, Rahane pulls it through square leg for a single.
Length delivery on middle, Sharma flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. Moves to 149, does Mr. Sharma. One run away from an amazing feat.
Full ball on middle, Rahane flicks it through square leg for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Rahane comes down the track and looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Flighted ball on middle, Rahane flicks it through square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Rohit keeps it out.

150 FOR ROHIT SHARMA! Wow! WHAT. AN. INNINGS. Rohit Sharma has spewed venom from his blade and has also reached his milestone now. He was in when India was in a spot of bother and has pulled them out of this hole and has put them in a commanding position. There were also talks after the first Test match, that Rohit needs to be dropped and replaced with someone else but Sharma has responded to his haters, in the best possible way, by keeping quiet and then letting his willow do all the talking. There is applause all around the ground and the Indian dressing room is on their feet. This is a fantastic way for Sharma to welcome the crowds back into the ground as well. Flatter and on the pads, Sharma flicks it through square leg and gets to this feat with a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Floated ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Sharma defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Rohit defends it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Sharma defends it off the front foot.
Floated ball on off, Rohit offers a solid defense on this one.
On off, Sharma pushes it towards covers for a single.
Short delivery on off, Rahane punches it to point.

Tossed up delivery on off, Rohit looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
BEATEN! Floated delivery down the leg side, Rohit looks to flick but misses it.
On middle, Sharma keeps it out.
Tossed up ball on off, Rohit defends it off the back foot.
On middle, Sharma comes down the track and flicks it towards short leg where Pope gets hit on the body. He looks to be fine though.
Shortish and on middle, Rahane goes on the back foot and whips this one through square leg for a single.
Darting on leg, Sharma looks to flick this one to the leg side but misses and gets rapped on the pads.

FOUR! Beautiful use of the feet and Sharma also brings up the 150-run stand between these two. Wonderful show. Full and flighted around middle, Sharma puts on his dancing shoes and slams this one over the mid on region and into the ropes, after a couple of bounces.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Full, loopy, on middle, Sharma gets on his knees and sweeps this one over the short fine leg region. Two runs before the fielder can run and stop this one.

NOT OUT! Sharma survives but this one was mighty close. Flighted and around off, spins away as Sharma comes on the front foot looking to block this one out but he misses. Foakes collects the ball and then whips the bails off in a flash and he seems very excited. Replay rolls in and it is very close. The foot was very close to just being on the line and the third umpire has a couple of looks at this one, from two different angles as well. After a while, he is ready with the decision and the big screen shows a big...NOT OUT!
Full delivery on middle, Sharma flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Floated ball on off, Sharma blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Sharma keeps it out.
Short delivery on off, Sharma punches it through point for a couple.
Down the leg side, Sharma looks to flick but misses it.
On the pads, Sharma flicks it towards short leg.
FOUR! No use running behind this one as Rahane has slammed this one. Fractionally short and around off, Rahane camps back and hammers this one through point and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Gets on the front foot and defends this one nicely towards the point region.
The broom is out now. Flighted and on off, Rahane sweeps this one to the deep square leg region for a single.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, England has done enough to break this stand. Rohit wanted to send this one all the way over the ropes and into the stands but his timing on this stroke was not the best. He is very unhappy with himself as he walks back now but there is applause all around the ground, as they show their appreciation to Sharma, who has been absolutely phenomenal with his 161. Flighted and on middle, Sharma looks to employ the sweep again, which he has played well so far. This time though, he ends up generating a top edge and the ball flies towards Moeen Ali at deep mid-wicket, who does not make a mess of this one. A delightful knock comes to an end and the 162-run stand is broken.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pant defends it off the back foot.
Floated ball outside off, Pant looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
Loopy delivery on off, Pant keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Pant defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Pant pushes it back uppishly towards the bowler where it falls short of Moeen Ali.
Flighted delivery on off, Pant keeps it out.
Flighted and on middle, Rahane comes on the front foot and keeps this one out.

NOT OUT! Rahane survives a scare now but he was very confident as he knew that he had not nicked that one.Â Flighted this time again and on the pads, Rahane looks to tuck this one away but to the naked eye, it looks like he has missed it and it has come off the pads and lobbed towards Pope at short leg, who collects the ball and appeals. The umpire is unmoved and the English players converged and Root makes the 'T' symbol. Ultra Edge rolls in and it is seen that there is no spike as the ball passes the bat. Will be not out. But it looks like Joe Root wants to check if this one was gloved, after it hit the pad as well. The third umpire also has a look if this could be lbw but it was pitching outside leg.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
Shortish and around off, pushed to the cover region now.
Comes on the front foot and blocks it out.
On middle, swept to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Rahane looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.

OUT! CASTLED! Rahane goes now. Root was annoyed that he was not given out in the last over and now, Rahane is walking back. England doing well to come back into the game now as they have removed those two set batters who were troubling them. Loopy and around the off pole, Rahane gets on his knees again and looks to sweep this one away but he does not connect the bat with ball on this occasion. The ball sneaks in under the bat and spins back in sharply to disturb the timber behind.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ashwin defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Ashwin keeps it out.
Full delivery on middle, Ashwin drives it towards mid on for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Pant keeps it out.
Skips down the track and bangs this one past the mid on fielder and Ashwin collects a brace as Root chases this one down.
On middle, nudged to the square leg region for a quick run.

FOUR! With Rishabh Pant at the crease, expect entertainment and some more entertainment. Gets off the mark with a boundary too. Shortish and outside off, Pant leans back and slaps this one through point and into the ropes in the deep.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Flighted and on off, Pant gets low and sweeps this one to the backward square leg region for a single.
Outside off, flighted, left alone by Ash.
Flighted and on leg, spins back in sharply as Pant blocks it with his body.

SIX! SLAMMED AWAY! Pant only knows how to play one way! Brilliant hit! Flighted and on off, Pant skips down the track and bangs this one away to the deep mid-wicket fence and into the stands.
On off, worked to mid-wicket.
Comes on the front foot and defends this one out.
Short, on off, Pant flicks this one through mid-wicket for a single.

EDGY. Flatter and on middle, Ashwin looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge and lobs in front of him to land safe.
On middle, Ashwin goes to sweep but the ball takes the top edge and goes over the short fine leg region for a brace.
On off, played to point for a couple again.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler. Root collects and throws it back towards the keeper as Ashwin moves away. The crowd does not like that and is quick to voice their opinion.
Tossed up delivery on off, Pant keeps it out.
Flighted ball on off, Pant defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pant blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice improvisation! Tossed up delivery on off, Pant plays a reverse sweep through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Good shot! Loopy ball on off, Pant comes down the track and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.

NOT OUT! Pant went for the review straightaway and it works out in his favor. Flatter and around off, Pant goes on the back foot and looks to block this one out but he misses and Foakes collects the ball. An appeal and the on-field umpire raises his finger. Pant goes for the review straightaway and replays show that there is no bat. The on-field decision has been overturned.
Tossed up delivery on off, Ashwin defends it to point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Root gets a wicket now. England doing well to scalp some good wickets right towards the end of the day. This is flighted and around leg and middle, Ashwin is in two minds in whether to defend this one or to flick it to the leg side. In the end, he comes ahead and the ball takes the inside edge, then the pads and goes to Pope at short leg, who takes a good catch.

It has come off the back of the bat and lobbed to Kohli. He dives forward and takes the catch nicely. The onfield call will be changed.

Flat and around off, Leach stays back to block.
Loopy and outside off, Leach is solid in defense.
Shortish and around off, Leach moves across and looks to block but the ball spins away. It goes off the outer half towards point.
On off, solidly blocked.
This time Foakes comes forward and pushes it to the right side of Ashwin who moves that side quickly to stop the ball.
Full and around off, flicked through mid-wicket for one.
Floated on middle, Leach defends. It goes uppishly but wide of the man at silly point.
Forces him on the back foot this time and bowls it just outside off. Leach blocks well.
Full and around off, solidly defended again.
Floated full and around off, poked towards point.
Spins in after pitching on middle. Foakes looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad.
Loopy ball outside off, driven wide of mid off for an easy single.
Floated delivery on off, Leach keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Leach defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Good shot! Tossed up delivery on off, Leach comes down the track and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
Floated delivery on off, Foakes keeps it out.
Tossed up ball on middle, Foakes defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Foakes sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Leach defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on off, Leach pushes it to mid off.
Turn and bounce on this one! Googly outside off, Leach looks to sweep but misses it due to the sharp turn on this one.
Full delivery on off, Foakes defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up ball on middle, Foakes flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Leach defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on off, Leach blocks it off the front foot.
On off, Leach pushes it through point for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Foakes looks to defend but gets an inside edge. It goes towards short fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Loopy delivery on off, Foakes looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads.
Full toss on middle, Foakes sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Leach keeps it out.
Floated outside off, Leach offers no shot to this one.
Loopy delivery on off, Leach keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Leach keeps it out.
On middle, Foakes flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Leach looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up delivery on off, Leach blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Leach defends it off the back foot.
On middle, Leach offers a solid defense on this one.
FOUR BYES! Tossed up delivery down the leg side, Leach looks to flick but misses it. It goes past the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on middle, Foakes looks to flick but gets an inside edge. It goes towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
BEATEN! Googly outside off, Leach looks to defend but misses it.
Full delivery on off, Leach defends it to covers.
Floated ball on off, Leach pushes it to point.
On off, Leach taps it towards the off side.
Flighted delivery on off, Leach blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Foakes pushes it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Leach looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes safely towards gully.
FOUR! Good length delivery on off, Foakes looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes past the gully fielder towards third man for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Foakes drives it through point. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs. England have avoided the follow-on.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another stunner from Pant. One-handed blinder from Pant. A good length ball, shapes away after pitching. Leach looks to defend with hard hands. He ends up getting a thick outside edge, the ball flies to the left of the keeper. Pant flies to his left again. The ball once again sticks in his left hand. Fine, fine catch and India just 1 away from bundling England away. A probing over from Ishant this one and he finally gets the reward.
Beaten first ball. Lovely from Ishant. This is just outside off on a good length. Broad has to play at it. He does that but the ball goes away to beat the outside edge.
Flighted delivery on off, Foakes keeps it out.
Short ball on off, Foakes punches it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Loopy delivery on off, Foakes defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Foakes pushes it through mid on for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! There you go! It's all over in this innings. Fifer for Ashwin! His 29th in Tests. Floated on middle, Broad gets down and looks to sweep. He fails to get under it and ends up getting an inside edge. The ball then hits his pad and goes onto the stumps. England are bowled out for 134.
Full delivery on off, Sharma defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on middle, Rohit flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, Sharma offers no shot to this one.
Rohis is up and running! A fuller ball on middle, Rohit flicks it through mid-wicket. The man from deep square leg gets to his left and stops. Two for Rohit.
Back of a length on off, Rohit keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Sharma pushes it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Gill defends it off the back foot.
Floated ball on off, Gill pushes it to point.
Loopy delivery on off, Gill pushes it to covers.
Outside off, Gill shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on off, Gill lofts it over point. The batsmen get two runs.
Floated ball on middle, Gill flicks it to square leg.
Length ball outside off, Rohit offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Sharma drives it to mid off.
Back of a length on off, Rohit keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma offers no shot to this one.
SIX! Take that! WOW! That is powerful strike from Rohit. Stone bangs it short and it is on middle. Rohit transfers his weight on the back foot and nails it over deep square leg for a biggie.
Length delivery on off, Rohit pushes it to point.
Tossed up delivery on off, Gill defends it off the front foot.
Flighted ball on off, Gill blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Gill defends it off the back foot.
Floated ball on middle, Shubman looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up delivery on off, Gill pushes it to covers.
Flighted delivery on off, Gill comes down the track and lofts it over mid off. The batsmen get two runs.
FOUR! Punched nicely and Moeen gets a welcome with a boundary. He drops the first ball short and bowls it wide as well. Rohit punches it through the covers and finds the fence.
Loopy delivery on off, Sharma look to defend off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated on middle, Sharma sweeps it through square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Googly outside off, Gill looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
BEATEN! Tossed up outside off, Gill looks to push but misses it.

SIX! Gill connects this one alright. 2nd six of the innings. Indians have cleared their intent here. Leach tossed it up and landed it around middle and leg. Gill comes down the track and hammers it over long on for a biggie.
Floated delivery on off, Sharma defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Fine shot! Tossed up and on middle, Rohit moves inside the crease and paddles it uppishly through short fine leg. The man from deep square leg runs to his right and looks to stop but the ball wins the race to the fence.

FOUR BYES! Turn and bounce for Leach there. It pitches outside off, Rohit is drawn forward as he looks to defend. The ball lands on the rough and turns away. Bounces extra to beat the keeper and Stokes at first slip as well. Races away to the third man fence. Given byes.
Loopy delivery on off, Rohit keeps it out.
Tossed up ball on off, Sharma blocks it off the front foot.
Floated around off, kept out off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Gill looks to defend off the front foot but gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up outside off, swept to deep square leg for one.
Pitches outside off. Slightly short. It spins in. Rohit goes on the back foot and clips it to square leg for one.
Flat and on middle, worked through mid on for one.
Another easy single. This one once again spins in from outside off, Rohit tucks it through square leg for one.
Tossed up and outside off, Gill comes down the track and looks to defend but gets hit on the pad.

NOT OUT! The desperate dive saves Rohit. There wasn't a run there. Full and outside off, Rohit pushes it towards backward point. Rohit wants the single but is sent back. The fielder from gully quickly gets to the ball and throws it to the keeper. Foakes takes the bails off. The third umpire has been called for. Replays roll in and it shows that Rohit has made it in with the dive.
Tossed up delivery on off, Sharma defends it off the front foot.
Floated ball on off, Sharma looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip where it falls short of Ben Stokes.
On middle, Sharma keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Sharma sweeps it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated ball on off, Gill keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Sharma flicks it to mid-wicket.

Chance! Stumping chance but Foakes fells to collect the ball. Leach tosses it up and just outside off. Rohit dances down the track and looks to go big but the ball lands and spins in. He misses to connect. Foakes cannot collect the ball to his left. It was a touch take and Ben failed to collect it. How costly will this be for England?
BEATEN! Loopy delivery outside off, Sharma looks to cut but misses it.
BEATEN! Googly outside off, Sharma looks to defend but misses it.
Floated delivery on off, Sharma blocks it off the front foot.
This one keeps low. Rohit looks to cut but misses. The keeper fails to collect and the ball goes towards fine leg. A bye taken.
Floated around off, Rohit keeps it out off his front foot.
Comes down the track and pokes it towards point this time.
Edgy! Floated outside off, Rohit comes on the front foot and looks to defend. The ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of the slip fielder.

Confusion again but safe again! Rohit taps this shortish ball to the left of the backward point fielder and he takes off for the run. Gill sends him back as the fielder quickly gets to the ball and throws it to the keeper. Rohit is back in time.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Floated just around off, Gill defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Gill looks to sweep but gets a top edge. It goes towards square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Loopy delivery on middle, Gill looks to defend but misses it and gets hit on the pads.
Full ball on middle, Gill flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on off, Gill blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on leg, Gill looks to play the reverse sweep but misses it. It goes past the keeper towards fine leg for byes. The batsmen take three runs.
Floated ball on off, Gill defends it off the front foot.

OUT! LBW! Three reds! Gill departs and takes the review along with him. Leach gets the breakthrough. Flighted delivery on off, Gill looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his finger. Gill reviews it at the last second. Ultra Edge detects no spike on it. Ball Tracker shows that it is three reds.
Floated delivery on off, Pujara defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on off, Pujara punches it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
On middle, Rohit defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rohit flicks it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Sharma looks to sweep but gets hit on the helmet.

NOT OUT! Impact is outside off! Flighted delivery on off, Sharma looks to defend off the front foot but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. England review it. Ultra Edge detects there is no spike on it. Ball Tracker shows that impact is outside off. England lose their review.
Tossed up and outside off, swept to square leg for one.
Floated outside off, poked towards point.
Full toss on middle and leg, Pujara flicks it hard but cannot go past the man at mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, it is kept out. Good testing over from Moeen.
Flighted delivery on middle, Sharma defends it off the back foot.

NOT OUT! There is indeed an inside edge! Floated delivery on off, Sharma looks to play the reverse sweep but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his finger. Rohit reviews it. Ultra Edge detects a spike on this one. Good use of the review from Rohit.
Full and on middle, Rohit flicks it through mid-wicket for one.
Floated outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Around off, Pujara keeps it out.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off and Pujara is not going to miss out. He rocks back and punches it through backward point to find the fence. 50 up for the Indians
Tossed up delivery on off, Sharma looks to defend off the front foot but gets hit on the pads.
Floated ball outside off, Sharma looks to sweep but misses it.
Flighted delivery on off, Sharma comes down the track and pads it away.
On middle, Rohit sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery outside off, Pujara looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Outside off, Pujara pads it away.
On middle, worked towards square leg.
Shortish and just outside off, poked towards backward point for nothing.
Floated on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! A close call but Rohit kept his back leg inside the crease. Tossed up and just outside off, Rohit is drawn forward. The ball spins away to beat the outside edge. Foakes collects and takes the bails off quickly. They appeal and the third umpire has been called for. Replays roll in and it shows that Rohit's back leg is in.
Full and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Full and around off, pushed to mid on for nothing.
Floated on middle, kept out.
On off, pushed to mid off this time.
On the pads, Pujara pads it away.
Shortish and around off, this time it is pushed towards the cover region.
Turn again! This one pitches outside off, spins in. Pujara is down the track to defend. Misses to get hit on the pad and it lobs on the off side. A mild appeal but turned down.
Floated around off, Rohit comes on the front foot and defends it towards silly point.
Rohit comes down the track and blocks.
Flat and just outside off, defended towards second slip off the back foot.
Rohit dances down the track this time and tucks it wide of mid on for a single.
Shortish and around middle, Pujara stays back to block it.
Floated around off, Pujara comes on the front foot to bunt it on the leg side. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Run straightaway! Ali floats the first ball on middle, it spins in a touch. Rohit clips it through square leg for a single.
Turn but the line is not right. Moeen once again lands it around middle, it spins in and beats the flick of Pujara.
This time Pujara dances down the track and works it towards square leg. Rohit says no for the run.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Floated around off, Pujara defends it nicely.

OUT! RUN OUT! Pujara is short. Oh, dear! What an unfortunate way to get dismissed. You got to feel for Pujara. His bat got stuck in the crease and he failed to return back. Moment of luck for England early in the morning. Moeen loops it up and around off and middle, Pujara comes down the track and flicks. Pope at short leg is alert. He stops the ball quickly and throws it to the keeper who takes the bails off. The third umpire has been called for. Replays roll in. Pujara tries to get back but his bat gets stuck in the crease and then he tries to return but ends up being on the line. And that is enough for the third umpire to send him back to the pavilion. Unfortunate way to get dismissed.
Tossed up on middle, tucked towards short fine leg.
Floated on middle, Rohit comes on the front foot to block.
Loops up around off, turns away. Rohit looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge. Stokes dives to his right to stop the ball.
On off, Rohit is solid in defense.
Fullish and on middle, Rohit flicks uppishly towards mid-wicket.
This time he takes a big stride forward and defends solidly.
Flat and around off, spins in. Kohli comes on the front foot to block.
Sharp spin. It lands on the rough and spins in. Kohli looks to defend but misses to get hit on the body.
This time Moeen loops it up. Kohli comes on the front foot and bunts it onto the pitch.
Short but slower through the air. Kohli is early in the pull to miss out on a scoring opportunity.
Tossed up and outside off, kept out.
Once again a solid front foot defense presented by the Indian skipper. Good, testing over from Moeen again.

OUT! STUMPED! Very sharp work from Foakes and England have sent both the overnight Indian batters back to the pavilion. Superb delivery from Leach. Rohit walks back now. Leach tosses the ball just outside off, Rohit lunges forward and looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge. Foakes collects and takes the bails off in a flash. The third umpire has been called for again. And Rohit's foot is on the line, feels the third umpire. Nothing behind the line and OUT flashes on the big screen. The centurion from the first innings has to go.
He is off the mark in a streaky fashion. Floated just around off, it spins away. Pant looks to force it on the off side but it takes the outer half and goes through backward point for one.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Comes on the front foot and solidly blocks.
Loopy and just outside off, long stride forward again and a solid block.
This one is flat and just outside off. Kohli goes back to punch it on the off side. End of a successful over for England and Leach.
Quicker one around the pad on a slightly shorter length. Pant defends off the back foot.
In the air... safe! It was a full toss on middle, Pant goes for the sweep but ends up miscuing it. It goes wide of the man at short fine leg. Two taken.
On middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler this time.
Shortish and just outside off, turns away. Pant waits and punches it towards backward point. Thinks for a single but Kohli says no.
Pant wanted to come down the track and adjusted in the end as Moeen darted a flat one around off. Pant defends.
On middle and leg and shortish in length. Pant goes back and works it towards the leg side.
Loopy ball outside off, Kohli drives but finds mid off. 11 balls and nothing for the Indian skipper so far.
Full and on middle, Kohli flicks it nicely but once again finds the fielder. This time it goes to square leg.
Looped up outside off, turning away. Kohli lets it be.
Loopy and around off, Kohli is on the front foot to block.
Beats him this time with the one that lands on theÂ rough around off and turns away. Kohli was on the front foot to defend.
Flat and around middle, Kohli flicks it to the man at square leg.
Good running! Flat and around off, turns away. Pant pokes it towards the off side. Kohli calls for the single. Pant responds and they get it easily in the end.
Turn again! Pitches around off and spins in. Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
On middle, flicked towards square leg.
Fuller and around off and middle, worked towards the same fielder again.
He is off the mark on the 20th ball. A flat ball around off, spinning in. Kohli this time goes on the back foot and tucks it through short fine leg for a brace.
Floated around off, Kohli comes on the front foot to defend solidly.
Quicker one on middle, tucked towards square leg.

FOUR! Not where he wanted to hit but Pant will take it. First boundary of the morning. Tossed up and outside off, Pant gets down and looks to sweep. The ball spins in. It takes the gloves and goes to the right side of the keeper. Races away to the fine leg fence.

OUT! STUMPED! Foakes with a stunning work again and Pant falls now. He was always going to play his shot but falls in the process. Leach tosses it up and outside off, Pant dances down the track but fails to reach to the pitch properly. And the ball lands in the rough and spins in to beat his attempt. It goes to the right side ofÂ  Foakes who collects the ball and whips the bails in a flash. Pant walks back now and the morning keeps getting better.
Full and around off, Rahane looks to defend but it goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Rahane is beaten this time. Pitches just outside off and spins away as Rahane looks to block off the front foot.

Just short! Rahane would've had his heart in his mouth. This one was short and it spun away. Rahane looks to cut but fails to connect it well. It goes uppishly to Stone at backward point but it falls short. Eventful over ends.
Tossed up and around off, spins in. Kohli comes on the front foot to block.
Full and around off, Kohli whips it using his bottom hand but finds mid on.
Short ball, slower through the air. It is outside off. Kohli pulls it hard but cannot beat the man at mid-wicket.

FOUR LEG BYES! Welcome boundary for India. This one turns in, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but it keeps low. Hits his pad and races away to the fence at fine leg. That came off the bat clearly as the replays suggested but given leg byes by the umpire.
Floated around off, pushed to mid off.
Quicker and around off, worked on the leg side.
Edgy! Shortish and just outside off, Rahane rocks back and looks to cut but ends up getting an under edge. It hits the pad of the keeper and goes to mid-wicket. A single taken.
Full ball around off, pushed to the cover region.
On off, Kohli comes on the front foot to block.

Uppish but safe! Burns flew to his left and maybe got fingertips to it. Tossed up and outside off, Kohli drives it uppishly. The ball goes wide of the man at covers who dives to his left but fails to catch. Three taken as the ball stops nears the fence.
Rahane goes for the sweep this time. Fails to connect it off the middle and it goes towards the leg side off the inner half. A single taken.
Flat and around off, kept out off the back foot.
Floated outside off, Rahane takes a long stride forward and looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. The impact is well outside off so no appeal.
Looped up and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Big, big turn! Like a cobra this one. It pitches short and outside off. Lands on a rough and spins in sharply. Rahane goes on the back foot and somehow manages to fend it off.
FOUR! Freebie from Moeen and Rahane will not miss out. A full toss just around off, Rahane takes a step forward and nails it through the covers to find the fence. Poor from Moeen.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries to Rahane and India. After a full toss, Moeen drags his length short and around middle and leg. Rahane rocks back and hammers the pull through square leg for a boundary.
Good ball to end the over! Draws the batsman forward with a loopy ball. It spins in and Rahane is hit high on the pad.
Floated around off, poked towards backward point.
Leading edge! Floated full delivery and around off, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but it takes the leading edge and goes uppishly past the man at silly point.
On off, kept out.
Darted outside off, left alone.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Kohli will take it. Floated outside off, Kohli comes on the front foot and looks to defend but with soft hands. The ball takes the outer half and goes past the man at backward point. Stone gives it a chase, reaches out with a slide but ends up pushing it into the fence at third man as he tries to pick up the ball. Poor work.
Flat and around off, turns in. Kohli stays back to defend.
Tossed up and outside off. Rahane comes down the track and makes it into a full toss. Pushes itÂ towards the cover region in the end.
On middle, kept out.

OUT! TAKEN! Fine catch at short leg and Rahane walks back now. Moeen gets his first wicket. HalfÂ the Indian team back to the pavilion now. Moeen slows this one and lands it outside off. Rahane comes down the track to defend with his bat and pad together. This one doesn't turn much and Rahane ends up getting it off the inner half of the bat. It then hits his pad and lobs uppishly in front of Pope at short leg. The master of short leg catching, Pope, dives forward and takes the catch inches above the turf. The umpire raises his finger and Rahane goes. India lead by 281 at the moment.
Floated around off, kept out off the front foot.
Short and just outside off, Patel punches it well but finds the cover fielder.
Full and around off, kept out safely off the front foot. End of another successful over for England.
First bad ball from Leach and Kohli is onto it in a flash. Punches it through backward point and gets three. Kohli is into the double digits.
Floated outside off, Patel looks to drive but it goes to mid-wicket off the inner half. A single taken.
Short and just outside off, Kohli goes on the back foot and flicks it through mid-wicket. The long on fielder gives it a chase and stops it near the fence. Two for Kohli.
Loopy and around off, Kohli is on the front foot to dead bat it.

FOUR! BOOM! Shot of the morning. Kohli finding is mojo here. Tossed up and on middle, Kohli uses the bottom hand and whips it through mid on for a boundary. The man at mid on had no chance to react to his left.
