Flicks this one towards mid-wicket and says no for the run. A good over for the Indians. 10 off the over.
Full and on middle, kept out.
Floated outside off, Axar comes on the front foot to defend. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the short third man region. Quick single taken.
Short and outside off, tucked towards the leg side.
Floated outside off, spinning in. Kohli comes on the front foot and manages to tuck it towards short fine leg.
Dropped short again. This time he goes deep in the crease to work it towards the leg side.
On the pads, this time Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
Flighted and full on off, Axar is forward as he works it with the spin to short mid-wicket.
Beaten! Patel looks to defend it with the spin but this one goes straight on to beat the outside edge.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Uses his feet this time and flicks a full ball across the line, finds short mid-wicket.
Flatter and shorter on middle, Axar gets the chance to go back and help it behind square leg for a run.
Nicely flighted and full on middle, Virat leans forward and defends it close to his front pad.
Flighted and full around off, Patel defends it off the front foot.
Turning away from the batsman, Axar is beaten as he tries to defend off the front foot.
Another play and a miss! Spinning away from around off, Patel gets back and pushes at it but it turns to beat the blade.
And again, Patel is beaten as he fails to deal with the delivery spinning away from his willow.
Fuller and on off, Patel defends it from the middle of the bat.
FOUR! 100 up for India! Slightly short and on middle, turning away, Axar goes on the back foot, uses his wrists and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flat and just outside off, Kohli stays back to block.
Floated around off, Kohli pokes it towards the cover region off the front foot.
Goes on the back foot and blocks it towards the off side again.
Full and around off, kept out.
Beaten! But got to give it to Kohli for not chasing the spin. He stays back and allows the ball to turn and then looks to defend. Misses but is beaten by some distance.
FOUR! And he won't miss out on the scoring opportunity. Leach bowls a full toss on the pads, Kohli whips it through square leg and finds the fence. The lead goes up to 301.

OUT! LBW! No bat involved and umpire's call on hitting wickets. The onfield call stays and India lose their sixth wicket. Lovely from Leach. He slowed this one down and landed it around off. Patel comes on the front foot to defend but a hint of spin into the batsman means he misses to get struck on the pad. A loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger after taking a bit of time. Axar has a word with the skipper and decides to take it upstairs. Time for the replays. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball would clip the middle stump. So, Patel has to go. Review stays for the Indians though as it was the umpire's call.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Broom is out and the crowd loves it. It is the local boy. Tossed up and outside off, Ashwin gets down and nails the sweep through the mid-wicket region. Lovely shot to get off the mark.
On off, looks to drive this time but the ball spins in, takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket.
Flat and around middle, clipped to mid-wicket this time.

FOUR! Ashwin brings the reverse sweep now and bags another boundary. Tossed up and outside off, Ashwin plays the unconventional sweep and top edges it over short third man. The man from the ring gives it a chase and pulls it back as the batters take three. The third umpire has been called. And it has been given as a boundary. Stokes, the man who put in that effort, looks unhappy.
FOUR! BANG! Poor from Leach this time. Short and wide outside off, Kohli rocks back and thumps it through point to bag a boundary now. Runs flowing for India at the moment.
Floated around off, Kohli is on the front foot to block.
Pitches and turns away. Kohli stays back and taps it towards backward point. Kohli thinks for the single but no says his partner at the other end.
Once again he stays back as Leach drops it short and pokes it wide of the backward point fielder. This time they get the run.
This is darted outside off. Ashwin lets it be. Watches it all the way to the gloves of the keeper.
Floated around off, kept out.
Floats the first ball full and around off, Kohli blocks.
Full again. This one is on middle and leg. Flicked towards mid-wicket.
This time he flicks it wide of the man at mid-wicket and takes one.
Short and around middle, kept out off the front foot to mid off.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off. Wanted a single but opted against it.
Uppish but safe! Ashwin wanted to work it on the leg side but it came slower through the air. Ends up getting a leading edge which falls to the left of the bowler.
Beaten! Floated outside off, spins away. Kohli is on the front foot to block but misses. Good take from Foakes behind the sticks. The birthday boy is having a good time.
Pokes this one towards backward point and gets to the other end.
This time it keeps low and it is outside off. Ashwin does well to block.
Goes for the sweep this time but this one sneaks below his bat and goes to the keeper. It was pitched outside off and Ashwin made no connection as it went straight on.

This time Ashwin is to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over the man at mid on. Broad gives it a chase and puts in a fine sliding stop. Saves a run for his side, does Broad. Haven't got a chance to bowl but Broad is doing his best in the field.
Kohli stays back and eases it towards backward point. He is off for the single but Ashwin says no.
Almost dragged on! Flat and just outside off, spins in sharply. Ashwin gets an inside edge that goes past the stumps to leg slip.
Tossed up and on middle, Ashwin sweeps it hard. The man at square leg dives to his left but fails to stop. The fielder in the deep cuts it off and the batsmen take two.
On off, kept out.
Darted on the pad, blocked nicely.
Floated around off, Ashwin comes on the front foot to block it safely.
Ashwin sweeps it hard again but finds square leg who fumbles and they take one.
Very full and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Again very full and around off, pushed towards the cover region once more.
Tossed up and just around off, Ashwin backs away and looks to go inside out but ends up getting it high on the bat. It lobs towards the bowler but falls short.
FOUR! Swept and swept hard. Loopy and outside off, Ashwin gets down and nails the sweep through square leg. Plays it against the turn and finds the fence again. His 3rd boundary.
Flat and on middle, this time he flicks it through square leg. Two taken. Ashwin moves to 20 off just 24 balls. Playing a gem!
Turn and bounce and Ashwin is beaten as he lunges in defense. This will keep happening on this surface.
Flat and just around off, kept out.
Floated outside off, Kohli moves across on the off side and blocks.
Flat and around middle, flicked to mid-wicket for nothing.
Too full and on middle, Kohli flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Ashwin connects the sweep again. This is top stuff from him. He moves to 24 off 26 balls. Tossed up and around middle, Ashwin nails the sweep over the man at short fine leg for a boundary.
Floated outside off, kept out.
Big appeal but turned down. No review from England. Floated around off, Virat comes on the front foot and looks to defend but probably gets an inside edge on the pad.
Loopy and outside off, poked towards the off side.
Defends it solidly this time.
Another solid front foot block from Kohli as Leach bowls this one around off.
This time Kohli stays back as Leach drops it slightly short. It's kept out safely on the off side.

Now on the front foot. This is good from the Indian skipper. Leach tosses it up and bowls it outside off. Kohli comes on the front foot, smothers the spin and bunts it on the off side. Proper Test cricket style batting from the Indian skipper on this testing track.

FOUR! A length ball around middle, Ashwin clips it through short fine leg. The deep square leg fielder runs in and puts in a diving effort. The Indians take three. The third umpire is called to confirm if it is a clean stop. Looks like Leach is touching the rope at the time when he tries to push the ball back in. Yes, a boundary is given. So, Broad is welcomed into the attack with a boundary.
Full and outside off, pushed to the man at backward point.
Good length and around off, poked towards point.
Around off on a length, kept out.

EDGED BUT PUT DOWN! That flew to Stokes and he fails to snap it. It was the cutter from Broad, landed around off and went away as Ashwin looked to drive. The outside edge flew to the left of Stokes who reacted at first slip but failed to hold on. It deflected away and the batsmen crossed.
Bounce this time and Kohli is beaten on the outside edge. Good stuff from Broad. Shortish and just outside off, a hint of away movement. Kohli fails to defend. Foakes cannot gather it cleanly too.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for nothing.
On off, poked towards backward point for one this time.
Floated around off, Kohli is solid in defense.

FOUR! Nicely done! Full and on the pads, Kohli clips it through short fine leg and it races away to the fence. Didn't hit it too hard but the outfield is quick. The fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the races.
Full again. It is pushed to long on for an easy single. With men in the deep, easy singles on offer at the moment.
Floated on middle and leg, Ashwin blocks.
Outside off, left alone. Good take from Foakes behind the sticks. It was to his right and went a bit high too.
Good length and around off, poked towards backward point. Wanted a single but Ashwin was not interested.
Back of a length and around off, Kohli is solid in defense.
Outside off again. Kohli lets it be.
Good length and outside off, Kohli pushes it towards the backward point fielder.
Around off on a good length. Kohli is rock solid in defense again.

NOT OUT! Well, well! Why was this reviewed? A poorÂ one from Root and England. Big, big turn on the first ball for Lawrence though. It pitches on middle, on theÂ rough and spins down the leg sideÂ sharply. Ashwin looks to flick but misses. They appeal for a caught behind as Foakes collects the ball but the umpire stays put. Root thinks and then takes a late review after discussing with his boys. The replays show that there was a good social distancing maintained between bat and ball.
Low full toss, pushed towards the extra cover region for a quick single.
Floated outside off, Kohli pokes it towards backward point and gets to the other end.
Too full and wide outside off. Ashwin drills it through the covers and scampers back for three more.
Floated on middle, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Tossed up and wide outside off, Kohli drives it through the covers and gets two. The 50-run stand is up between the two and the lead now reads 351. And with this, IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 3.
A tossed up ball, an off spinner but on the shorter side, Ashwin hangs back and works it wide of short fine leg for a run.
Too full and close to off, Kohli brings his bottom hand into play and drills it to long on for one.
Full and flighted outside off, Ashwin draws well forward and defends it near his front pad.

Confusion over a run! Tossed up ball on middle, Ashwin is on the back foot as tickles it behind square leg. Kohli wants a run but Ashwin sends him back as the short fine leg fielder attacks the ball. There is a direct hit at the bowler's end but Virat is safely in by then.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Floated and full, around off, Ashwin flicks it off the inner half of his bat to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball on off, Kohli defends it solidly from the crease.
Virat stretches forward to a full ball outside off and blocks it safely.
Loopy and full, landing on middle, Kohli defends it right under his eyes.
Leach drags his length short around off and Kohli also drags his body inside the crease. He, then, punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Loopy but too full on off, Ashwin is forward as he defends it late.
Beaten this time! Turn and bounce from around off, Ashwin goes on the back foot and initially looks to push inside the line but then withdraws his bat as it spins past his blade.
Turns in from outside off and hits Kohli high on the pad as he misses to defend. Too high!
FOUR! A Kohli-special this time! Full and outside off, Kohli drills it through the covers and it races away to the fence.
Floated around off, kept out.
Short and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Short again, this one is outside off, Kohli stays back to block.
Fuller and around off, worked to the man at short leg.
Floated outside off, Ashwin keeps it out from the back foot. Does well to deal with the extra bounce there.
Short and outside off again. Ashwin is on the back foot to block.
Floated outside off, Ashwin this time dances down and looks to defend. Misses to get hit on the pad.
Flat and just outside off, tucked wide of mid on for one.
Flat and just outside off, Kohli blocks solidly.
On middle, short again. Kohli easily nudges it on the leg side. Although not in the gap.
Ashwin comes down the track and pokes it through covers for one.
Pitches on middle, turns in. Kohli goes back to work it on the leg side. Fails to connect. Foakes makes a fine take down the leg side.
Muted LBW appeal. Floated around off, Kohli comes on the front foot and looks to defend. Gets an inside edge on the pad.
Shortish and on middle, worked on the leg side for one.

FOUR! First time Kohli brings the sweep and bags a boundary. Tossed up and on middle, Kohli gets down and nails the sweep over square leg for a boundary. Moves to 48. You rarely see Virat play the sweep shot but he did practice it a lot before this Test match. Pulled it off with aplomb as well.
Floated outside off, Kohli goes back and blocks it towards the man at mid-wicket.
Shortish and outside off, punched towards the cover region.
Full and on middle, Ashwin flicks it to deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Floated full and around off, blocked solidly by stretching forward.
Quick single! A fuller one again. Kohli hits it to mid on hard but knows that the fielder is not on his heels. Takes off and completes the single easily. One shy of a brilliant half-ton.
Quicker one, it pitches and spins in sharply. Ashwin looks to defend but it takes the gloves and goes to short third man.
Full and around off, Ashwin is solid in defense as he draws forward.

FIFTY FOR KOHLI! His 25th in the format. In testing conditionsÂ where the others around him have struggled, the Indian skipper has delivered. A fine, fine knock from him. He has risen to the occasion and showed how it is done when the wicket spins. A shortish ball, it is outside off, he goes back and works it through mid-wicket for a single. Missed out in the first innings but the Indian skipper has stood tall here. A big round of applause from everyone in the stands.
On middle, Ashwin sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up and wide outside off, Virat goes back and blocks it with soft hands towards short third man.
Shortish and around middle, clipped through square leg for one.
Outside off, Ashwin comes forward, pokes it towards the off side and takes a single. Moves to 40 now.
Short and turning in. Kohli nudges it down to deep mid-wicket for one. 5 from the over, doing it with ease.
Tossed up and outside off, poked towards the cover region.
Full and around off, kept out off the front foot.
Loopy and outside off, Kohli prods forward and blocks.
Goes back and plays it back to the bowler this time as Leach drops it slightly short.
Dropped a bit short and once again Kohli pushes it to mid on off the back foot.

Drives it little left of the mid off fielder as Leach overpitches. Calls for a quick single and make it easily. The throw comes to the keeper and Foakes seems to have hurt himself while collecting the ball. Physio is out.
In the channel outside off to begin from Stone. Kohli shoulders arms.
Fullish and around off, punched straight back to the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, clipped to the man at mid-wicket.
Excellent running from Kohli. A shortish ball on middle, he flicks it wide of the man at fine leg. Calls for the second run and makes it easily in the end.
Good length and around off, this time Kohli taps it towards the off side. Wanted a single but Ashwin says no.
Short and just outside off, guided to the man at backward point.
Floated outside off, kept out.

Big turn! A superb take once again from Foakes. This one lands on the rough around off and middle, a big puff of dust comes off. It spins away like a cobra. Ashwin lets it be. Foakes shows his class as he collects it nicely to his right.
FOUR! Crunched! Poor from Leach. Dropped short and offered plenty of room as well. Ashwin says thank you very much and slams it through the cover-point region to bag another boundary.
On middle, kept out.
Flat and around off, Ashwin is solid in defense.
Around off, slightly short. Ashwin is on the back foot to block.
Shortish and around off, poked towards backward point.
Good length and around off, Kohli defends it back to the bowler.
A freebie and Virat will feel he missed out there. A high full toss. He just flicks it to fine leg for one.
A cross-court forehand by Ashwin. Australian Open is going on and Ash is showing his skills here in Chennai. Stone has banged it short and Ashwin slaps it down to long onÂ for two.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR ASHWIN! Through the off side. Ashwin is on the back foot again. Short ball outside off, he rocks back and whacks it through the covers and it races away to the fence. A fine, fine knock from the local boy. The crowd is up on its feet. His 12th Test half-ton and a very good one, coming in just 64 balls. Delivered with the ball in the first innings and is doing it with the willow here.
Short again but this one is down the leg side. Ashwin looks to pull but fails to connect. Foakes stops the ball to his left with a dive.
Floated short and around off, kept out.
Floated full and around off, Kohli defends solidly.
Slightly short and just outside off, punched towards the cover fielder.
Floated around off, Kohli is solid in defense again.
Short and wide, turning away. Kohli hits it through the covers and gets two.
Tossed up outside off, Kohli takes his front foot to the pitch of the ballÂ and plays a solid push to the cover region.
Short but down the leg side. Ashwin is expecting the shortish length. He moves inside and looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
Short and around off, pulled down to long on for one.
Banged short to Kohli as well. It is on middle, Kohli lets it go to the keeper.
Another short ball, this one keeps a touch low. Kohli pulls. It goes off the inner half to deep square leg for one.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Short and wide outside off, punched to the cover-point region. The Indian lead is now 389 runs.
Slower through the air and around off, turning in. Kohli nudges it wide of the man at short fine leg and takes one.
Full and around off, Ashwin blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated outside off, extra bounce as well. Ashwin looks to defend by getting forward and across but misses to get bat on ball.
Shortish and around middle, spins in. Ashwin tucks it to fine leg for a run.
Short and just outside off, poked towards the point region. Kohli comes ahead looking for aÂ run but is sent back.
Flat and just around off, worked on the leg side.
Fullish and around off, Ashwin punches it solidly but Broad makes a half stop.
Fullish and outside off, it pitches and then moves away. Ashwin fails to put the bat on the ball. Foakes fails to collect cleanly this time. Broad rolled his fingers on this one.
Leading edge but safe. A fuller ball, Ashwin looks to work it on the leg side but he ends up getting a leading edge. The ball goes uppishly but it is wide of the fielder at short cover.
Around off on a length, Ashwin looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to square leg. A run taken.
Shortish in length and around off, poked towards the man at backward point.
Shortish and just around off, Kohli stays back and blocks solidly.
Full toss outside off, swept to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full and wide outside off, Kohli looks to play the big-booming drive through the covers but fails to middle it well and finds the fielder.
On middle, this time he flicks it through square leg and moves to 61.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed to mid off for nothing by Ashwin.
Short and turning in, Ashwin works it through square leg and gets to the other end. 200 up for the hosts. The lead is now 395.
Floated on middle, Kohli flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes one to keep the strike for the next over.
Good length and outside off, fingers rolled. Kohli looks to defend but misses to connect. Good from Foakes once again behind the wickets.
Outside off this time and Kohli lets it be. Foakes fails to collect it cleanly this time.
Broad goes fuller and around off, Kohli defends it easily this time.
Around off on a length, pushed to backward point for nothing.
Outside off, left alone by Virat. Broad has a smile on his face.
Just outside off and on a good length. VK has his sticks covered as he lets it go to Foakes again. A sharp take from him again.
Extra bounce there. It floats on off and spins in with extra bounce. Ashwin manages to defend off his back foot.
Tossed up and outside off, eased through the covers for one now.
Fuller and around off, kept out.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets and Moeen has got his man again. Kohli has to depart. It is the 5th time that Moeen has got the better of Kohli in Tests. This is floated around off, slightly short. It spins in. Kohli looks to work it on the leg side from the back foot but misses to get struck on the pad. A loud appeal follows and the finger goes up.Â Kohli has a chat with his partner and then signals the 'T'. Replays roll in. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracker rolls in. It is umpire's call on hitting the wickets. So, the on-field call will stay. A brilliant, brilliant knock from the Indian skipper on this turning track comes to an end. The 96-run stand is broken and India lead by 397 runs.
Floated around off, Yadav pushes it to mid off.
Floated on middle, Kuldeep blocks it off the front foot. Successful over from Moeen.
Good length and around off, Ashwin blocks.
Fullish and around off, played back to the bowler.

Dropped! Foakes is the man. Such a good work from him so far but when the edge is drawn, Foakes fails to hold on. A rare miss from him. This is around off on a good length, Ashwin looks to guide it late but ends up getting a thick outside edge. It goes little right of Foakes who gets his gloves to it but fails to hold on.
FOUR! Nicely done! Insult to the injury. This is just outside off on a good length. Ashwin waits and then nicely opens the face of the bat to run it down to the third man fence. The lead crosses 400.
Pokes this one through the covers and gets to the other end now.
Length ball around middle, Kuldeep tucks it through square leg for a run.
Floated on middle, solidly defended by Kuldeep.
On middle once again, Kuldeep blocks it by drawing forward.
Floated around off, Kuldeep keeps it out nicely once more.
Lovely drive! Tossed up and outside off, driven through the covers for a brace. Kuldeep is no mug with the bat, has aÂ First Class hundred to his name.
Beaten this time! Lovely from Moeen. Lands it middle and leg on the rough. Spins away to beat the outside edge.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and Moeen has his 4th. Fuller and around off and middle, Kuldeep comes on the front foot and looks to defend but this one doesn't turn much. He though plays for it and misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal is made and the umpire has no problem raising his finger. It looked out but Kuldeep takes the review. Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows no bat. Time for the Ball Tracker. Here it comes. Pitching in line, impact in line and hitting the wickets. So, Kuldeep has to go. 8 down for India.
Short and wide outside off, Ashwin plays it to third man. Denies the single.
Around off on a length. Ashwin is solid in defense.

FOUR LEG BYES! Good length and outside off, Ashwin moves inside the crease and looks to paddle it over the keeper. Ashwin misses and the ball hits the keeper's leg and goes to the fine leg fence. Given leg byes.
Good length and around off, Ashwin blocks it this time.
Length ball around off, once again Ashwin is right behind the line in defense.
Outside off on a good length, Ashwin pokes it towards backward point. Thinks for aÂ single but Ishant says no as it went to the fielder quickly.
Very full and on off, Sharma digs it out off the inner half to leg gully.
Flatter and a touch short on off, Sharma defends it off his back foot.
Skidding away from the batsman, again on the shorter side but staying low, Ishant brings his bat down and keeps it out off the outer edge.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Full and flighted on off, Ishant is nicely forward as he defends it with soft hands.
Too full in length and on off, Ishant jams it out on the deck.
Good length ball around off, Ashwin punches it off his back foot to deepish mid off. No run taken.
A length delivery on middle and leg, Ashwin helps it behind square leg and returns for the second run.
Length ball on middle and off, Ashwin covers the line and offers a straight bat in defense.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Ashwin remains on the back foot and mistimes his punch back to the bowler.
Fuller length ball on middle and leg, Ashwin tries to flick but misses.

FOUR! Quality shot! Ravichandran Ashwin is showing his full repertoire. A lovely on drive from his blade. Full and on middle, Ashwin brings down a straight bat and creams it over mid on for a boundary. India lead by 415 runs.
Floated around off, turns in. Ishant looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the leg side.
Around off, Ishant is solid in defense this time.
Flat and around off, Ishant goes back to block.
Full and outside off, pushed back to the bowler.

Appeal from the keeper but nothing from Moeen. He feels it would've gone over. This one pitches outside off and spins in. Ishant is on the back foot. He looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
Looped up and outside off, driven to mid off for nothing. Ishant sees off another Moeen over.
Outside off on a good length, Ashwin looks to defend but is beaten on the inside edge.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards point.
Shortish and around middle, Ashwin works it to deep mid-wicket. Says no for the run.
Broad bowls a fine yorker but Ashwin is ready for it. He digs it out nicely.
Short and wide outside off, Ashwin dabs it down to third man for a single.
Full and wide outside off, Ishant keeps it out nicely. With this, IT IS TEA ON DAY 3.
Moeen starts with a floated delivery on the pad. Ashwin flicks it to square leg.
First runs of the session! Short around off, Ashwin punches it through extra cover and gets a couple.

Stumping opportunity missed! Foakes, who has been brilliant in this game has missed a stumping. Floated delivery outside off, Ashwin comes down the track and looks to go big but misses. The ball keeps low and kind of wrong-foots Foakes. He is unable to get down and collect the ball. There is a noise and Ultra Edge later shows that there was a little spike as the ball went past the bottom edge of the bat. A tough chance but from what we have seen from Foakes in this Test, he will be gutted to have missed that.
Floated on off, Ashwin blocks it.

In the air but in no man's land. Tossed up on off, Ashwin comes down the track and looks to go over on the on side. He does not time it well but gets a lot of height on it. Luckily for the local lad, the ball falls between the fielder coming in from the deep and the one running behind. Single taken.
Well defended. Flighted around off, the ball keeps low but Ishant keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it late off his back foot.
Broad starts with a fuller ball on off and middle, Ashwin defends it to mid on.
Full on off, Ashwin pushes it to cover.
On off, kept out.

FOUR! The ploy looks clear, Ashwin is trying to get to his century as quickly as possible and then India might declare. Fuller around off, Ashwin goes over mid off and gets a boundary. The local boy moves to 75 with that.
On the pads, Ashwin once again takes the aggressive route and flicks it over square leg. There is protection in the deep so just a run.
Ishant takes a single and gets off the mark in this Test. On the pads, Ishant flicks it to the leg side and keeps the strike with one.
Darted full on off, Ishant jams it out.
FOUR! Ishant is taking on the bowlers as well now. Flighted on off, Ishant comes down the track and lifts it over cow corner for a boundary.
Darted quicker and fuller outside off, Ishant looks to sweep but misses. There is a stifled appeal but the impact was well outside off.
On the pads, Ishant turns it behind square leg for a brace.
On the stumps, kept out by Ishant.
Slightly shorter on off, Ishant defends it off his back foot.
Leach starts with a shorter delivery on middle and leg, Ashwin pulls it off his back foot to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on off, Ishant defends it.
Flighted on middle, Ishant looks to defend and does so off the outer half of his bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! Leach gets his fourth and the bowling change has worked for England. Flighted delivery on off, Ishant looks to go for a big hoick with a slog sweep. He does not connect it as it comes off the upper half of his bat. Stone at square leg, runs to his left and slides to take a very good catch. 9 down and Ashwin is unbeaten on 77. Can Siraj hang in there till Ashwin's century?
FOUR! Short and punished! It is on middle, Ashwin pulls it, and unlike the first ball of the over, this time he pulls it hard and in the gap for a boundary.
Around off, Ashwin dabs it to third man and gets a single to keep the strike.
On the stumps, RA blocks.
Short on off, Ashwin defends it.
Shorter on off, Ashwin punches it back to the bowler.
Ohh! Floated around off, Ashwin looks to sweep but it hits the bottom edge and stays on the off side of the pitch.

IN THE AIR...AND FOUR!Â  Good effort in the deep but the ball falls well short of the fielder. Floated around off, Ashwin connects well with the sweep this time. It goes high in the air and away to the left of deep backward square leg. The fielder there dives and gets his hands on the ball after the bounce. He though is unable to stop it and can just deflect it to the fence.
Darted fuller on off, Ashwin blocks it. Leach can have a crack at Siraj in the next over.
Beaten! Tossed up on middle, Siraj looks to defend but the ball turns away and squares up Siraj as it goes past his outside edge.
Huge cheer from the crowd as Siraj blocks it. Shorter on middle, Siraj defends it.
Another roar from the crowd as Siraj blocks this shortish ball off his back foot.
Floated around off, Siraj looks to defend but gets beaten.
Floated on off, Siraj defends it off the front foot.
Siraj survives! A huge respite for the crowd as they want to see their local hero to get a ton. Floated on off, Siraj defends it.
Floated outside off, kept out.
Tossed on the pads, Ashwin looks to play the reverse sweep. Gets an under edge and the ball goes very close to the stumps. Goes to fine leg and Ashwin crosses. Moeen has 4 balls to Siraj now.
He drops it quick and just around off, Siraj stays and blocks.
Darted around off, Siraj is solid on the back foot defense. The crowd loves it as well.
Floated outside off, spins in after landing on the rough. Siraj comes on the front foot to defend but the ball spins in to hit him high on the pad.
Fired short and around off, Siraj negotiates it with ease this time. And the crowd approves the same again.
Floated on off, Ashwin pushes it ti cover.
Turn and bounce on this one. It pitches on the rough around off. Ashwin looks to defend but the ball turns away and beats the outside edge.
Tossed up on the stumps, Ashwin blocks it.
Flighted on middle, Ashwin drives it straight down the ground but does not take the single.
FOUR! Nicely played! 250 up for India and Ashwin moves to the 90s! Short and spinning away, Ashwin cuts it nicely away from point and gets a boundary. Can he farm the strike now?
No he cannot! Siraj will face the next over. Darted fuller around middle and leg, Aswin sweeps it but straight to short fine leg.

This is the loudest cheer you could possibly hear. Siraj has taken a single. Floated on off, Siraj defends it square on the off side. He is holding his pose but Ashwin calls for a run and they get it with ease. Siraj has a huge smile on his face as he looks at Ashwin.
Floated on off, Ashwin pushes it to mid off.

SIX! Going, going, gone! That was six the moment it left the bat. Floated on off, Ashwin gets down on his knees and smokes his sweep over mid-wicket for a biggie. The sound it made as soon as it hit the bat was indication enough to know that was out of here. Ashwin moves to 97 now. The lead crosses 450.
Make that 99! Ashwin now just one away from what would be an outstanding century. Flighted on off, Ashwin drives it away from sweeper cover and gets a brace.

HUNDRED FOR ASHWIN! What a player! What an innings! The man with the ball has also done the job with the bat! Take a bow, sir! This is top quality knock. Floated delivery around off, Ashwin looks to go over on the off side but it goes off the outside edge over the slips and races away to the fence at third man. Ashwin sprints to the other end, removes his helmet and jumps in the air in pure jubilation. The crowd is on its feet as their local superstar has followed a 5-fer with an extraordinary ton. Siraj punches the air as well. Looked like he is happier than Ashwin is. Not an easy pitch to bat on but Ashwin has shown his class, temperament and technique to get a ton. All his teammates are on their feet as they know this is one of the best innings they have witnessed. 5th Test ton for the local lad.
FOUR LEG BYES! Darted quicker around leg, Ashwin looks to sweep but the ball goes off his pads down the leg side and to the fence.

Siraj is off the mark now! He is done with showing all the patience. Ashwin has got to the milestone and now Siraj wants to have some fun. Goes for the massive slog as Leach tosses it up and around off, he mistimes it off the inner half towards deep square leg for a brace.
Flat and just around off, solidly blocked.

SIX! How about that? How about that? What an amazing blow. One for the ages from Siraj. Leach tosses it up again. This time Siraj stays in the crease and powers it over long on for a biggie. Kohli loves it in the dressing room.
Just short. This one is short and around off and middle, Siraj defends it off his back foot. Not from the middle and it lobs short of the man at short leg.
Floated full and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Full and around middle and leg, Siraj plays the helicopter shot. Root at mid-wicket dives to his left and looks to catch but fails to hold on. They do not go for the single.
Full on off, Ashwin defends it calmly.
Good shot but well fielded. Full outside off, Ashwin drives it to the left of cover. The fielder there dives and saves runs for his side.
Full toss which is just under the waist height. It is around the pads, Ashwin manages to flick it away to deep square leg but does not take the single.
Short ball on off and middle, Ashwin pulls it to mid on.
Good length ball around off, Ashwin punches it to mid off.
Shortish ball around off, Ashwin pulls it to mid on.
Shorter around off, Siraj defends it off his back foot.
Floated outside off, Siraj comes down the track and looks to defend. He ends up getting an inside edge on the pad. The ball then goes to the off side and they take one.

Hits the helmet of England but does not count. Darted around leg, Ashwin looks to pad it away. It kisses his pad and then hits the helmet which is kept behind the keeper. But because Ashwin did not offer a shot, the penalty runs won't count.
On the pads, Ashwin flicks it to the leg side and shows faith in Siraj as he takes a single.
SIX! Cracking shot! Siraj is having a party at the moment. Leach is the one paying for that party and he will not like it one bit. Floated on off, Siraj smokes his slog over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Darted fuller on off, Siraj now shows good defensive technique and blocks it.
On the stumps, Ash blocks it.
Fuller on off, Ashwin pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball around off, Ashwin punches it through the off side and gets a couple.
Shorter on off, Ashwin pulls it to mid on.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! End of a fantastic innings and that will also be the end of India's innings. Ashwin's superb knock comes to an end and he walks off to a standing ovation, one which he rightfully deserves. Shortish ball just outside off, Ashwin looks to pull it on the leg side but gets a thick inside edge which sees the ball hit the stumps. INDIA ALL OUT FOR 286! ENGLAND NEED 482 TO WIN!
FOUR! Runs for Burns straightaway! Ishant slips the first ball down the leg side. Burns flicks it through square leg and bags a boundary first ball.
Uppish but in the gap! Two moreÂ for Burns. Fuller and outside off, Burns reaches out and pushes it through the gap between cover-point. Two taken.
Ishant lands this one around off and it comes back in. Burns looks to defend but gets hit high on the pad.
This time Ishant misses the line again and bowls it down the leg side. Burns fails to connect his flick. Pant puts in a dive to his right to collect.
Fuller and wide outside off, pushed towards the man at backward point
Good ball to end the over! Good leave too. This one is angled in from outside off. Burns is confident about his stumps as he allows Pant to collect.
Turn straightaway! Axar tosses the first ball and lands it on the rough just outside off. It spins away and beats the outside edge.
Floated full and on middle, flicked to square leg.
Floated around off, kept out.
Big turn again! Tossed up and outside off, lands and spins away sharply. Pant does well to collect it to his right.
Beats the bat again does Axar. Once again he is able to land it on the rough. Dom comes forward and looks to defend but it spins away to beat the outside edge.
Sibley this time is solid behind the ball to block it confidently. A maiden to begin from Axar.
Good length and angled in. Burns blocks nicely. on the off side.
Angled in from around off again. Burns is solid in defense.
Ishant continues to attack the stumps. Fullish and around off, kept out.
Ouch! A short one from Ishant. He is early in his attempt though and ends up getting off the toe end of the willow.
In the channel outside off, comes back in. Left alone by Burns.
Fullish and just outside off, Burns is solid behind the line to block nicely. Maiden from Ishant.

Beats the bat first ball. Lovely start from Ashwin. Darts it quicker and just outside off. Sibley looks to defend but misses to connect as it spins a touch away. Pant fumbles a couple of times but catches it in the end.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it wide of deep square leg for two.
Floated around off, Dom is on the front foot to block.
Loopy and around off, Sibley looks to work it on the leg side but it goes off the inner half towards the off side.
Flat and around off, this time he blocks it nicely.
Turn and bounce but good from Sibley. It pitches outside off and spins in with extra bounce. Sibley stays back to block.
Floated around off, kept out by Burns.
On middle, nudged on the leg side for an easy single.
Floated full and around off, Sibley is on the front foot to block.
Outside off, Sibley trusts the pitch and lets it be.
Fuller and just outside off, Dom keeps it out.
Extra bounce this time. It pitches around off and bounces extra. Sibley defends off the upper part of the bat.
Tossed up and outside off, it lands on the rough and goes away. Burns lets it go.
Full and on middle, played back to Ashwin this time.

Was there an edge? There was. A chance goes begging. Floated on middle, it spins away and takes the outside edge as Burns looks to defend. Pant cannot catch to his left. It hits his pad and goes over the slip fielders. A single taken. Ashwin is not pleased. If it had not hit Pant's pad, it was heading to the first slip fielder.
Uppish again! This one is fuller and around off, spins in. It takes the inner half and goes between short leg and leg gully. One more single.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tossed up and around off, Burns dances down the track and strokes it through mid on for a boundary.
On the pads this time. Burns clips it through square leg and bags two more. Eventful over ends.
Lovely ball again! Axar lands it full and on the rough. Pitches and bounces extra to beat the forward prod.
On middle, this time it is kept out.
Full and around off, Sibley looks to defend but it goes off the inner half to the leg side.
On off, Dom blocks.
Too full and Sibley drives it well. Silly point intercepts with his body.
Floated around off, Sibley is solid in defense.
Looped up and on middle, played back to the bowler.
Loopy and on middle, Burns goes for the sweep this time. Fails to middle and it goes to short fine leg.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy and around off, Sibley comes on the front foot to block.
Big turn! Big bounce! Good take! Ashwin lands it full and just around off, it spins away as Burns looks to defend. It goes to the left of the keeper and bounces extra. Pant does well to collect.
Floated outside off, poked towards backward point this time.
On off, poked towards the off side by Sibley.

OUT! LBW! This is as plumb as it could be. He has a chat with his partner at the other end and opts against the DRS. Axar darts this flat with the arm. It pitches around off and middle and skids in sharply. Sibley goes on the back foot and looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. A loud, loud appeal and the finger is raised. The Indians celebrate. The debutant gets the breakthrough for the Indians.
Darts the arm ball again. Lawrence looks to defend off the back foot but ends up getting an inside edge on the pad.
Beaten! Tossed up and around off, a touch of spin away and Lawrence is beaten.
Flat and on middle, Dan keeps it out off his back foot.
He is rooted on the back foot again as Axar bowls an arm ball around off. Lawrence keeps it out.
Dropped short and just outside off. Burns looks to cut but misses to connect. Good sharp take from Pant to his left.
kept out.
Loopy and on middle, tucked towards the man at short fine leg.
FOUR! Third boundary for Burns. Ashwin lands this down the leg side. Burns manages to tickle it fine down the leg side to find the fence.
Floated around off, Burns comes forward and pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! Swept and swept hard. Second boundary in the over. Ashwin tosses it up and on middle and leg. Burns gets down and nails the sweep through square leg for a boundary. Good, positive batting from Burns. He moves to 22 off 31 balls.
FOUR! Lawrence is off the mark with a fine boundary. Floated around off, Lawrence comes down the track and whips it through mid-wicket to get off the mark with a boundary.
On off, pushed towards the cover region.

FOUR! Another boundary! Cracking shot. Lawrence is using his feet to good effect. Axar tosses it up and around middle. Dan dances down and flicks it uppishly through mid-wicket to bag another boundary.
Flat and around off, punched on the off side.
Axar beats the outside edge this time. Pitches just outside off, goes away to beat the forward defense of Lawrence.
And again! This one skids off after pitching outside off. It turns away as well and Lawrence is beaten for the outside edge.
Big, big turn again! Ashwin lands this one on the rough and it spins away sharply to beat the outside edge again. Good for Ashwin.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid on. Rory wanted a single but Dan sends him back.
Flat and around of, played back to the bowler.
Quick single! Full and around off, Burns pushes it towards mid off and goes for a single. Siraj has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses.
Full and on middle, worked to the man at mid-wicket.
FOUR BYES! This one lands on middle and viciously spins away. Pant cannot do anything about it. It races away to the fine leg fence. No bat there as the umprie signals it as byes.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Quicker one and on middle, tucked uppishly towards the man at short leg. Bounces well in front.
Floated outside off, swept to fine leg for one.
On off, Lawrence looks to defend but the ball spins in and goes to the leg side off the inner half.
On off, kept out.
Loops this one wide outside off. Dan looks to drive but gets an inside edge. The ball goes to square leg and they cross.

Good stop in the slip by Rahane. Ashwin darts this short and just around off. This one doesn't spin and Lawrence is squared up a touch. An outside edge in induced. Rahane does well to dive to his right and stop the ball.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid off.
On off, kept out.
Full and on middle, tucked on the leg side for nothing.
SIX! BANG! Good execution from Lawrence. Ashwin tosses it up and around off, Lawrence puts the dancing shoes on and launches it over long on for a biggie.
Floated around off, pushed towards mid on for nothing.
Quicker one from Axar, Burns tucks it towards the leg side for one.
Loopy and outside off, Lawrence drives but hits the silly point fielder.
Floated around off and middle, pushed to mid on for nothing.
Floated just around off, turns away a touch. Lawrende looks to defend but is beaten.
On middle, tucked through mid-wicket for one.
Flat and on middle, kept out.
Floated around off, Dan comes on the front foot and looks to defend. Misses to get hit high on the pad.
Flat and around middle, pushed to the right side of the bowler. Ashwin stops with his leg but it goes away towards mid on. They do not go for the single.
Full and around off, blocked.
Floated on middle, Dan comes forward and pokes it to long on for one.
Floated on middle, pushed to mid on.

OUT! TAKEN! Ashwin strikes. Burns has been removed nicely. Lovely stuff from the local lad. Tossed up, around off and middle, it lands on the rough and spins away. Burns looks to work it on the leg side but ends up getting an outside edge. Kohli at second slip takes the catch nicely. Burns walks back after showing good intent.
Tossed up around off, Lawrence comes down the track and pushes it to mid on.
Flighted on off, Dan LawrenceÂ defends it off the front foot.

Spin and bounce on this one. It pitches on off and turns away from Lawrence. He gets on his front foot and looks to defend but misses. Pant behind the stumps fails to take it on the full. Would have been interesting to see as that was very close to the outside edge.
Floated on off, Dan LawrenceÂ keeps it out.
On the pads, Dan LawrenceÂ flicks it to the leg side and takes a run. Over to you, Leach!

OUT! CAUGHT! The nightwatchman walks out for a duck and Axar Patel gets his second wicket of the innings. The ploy to send the nightwatchman has not worked at all and England have lost their 3rd wicket. Sharp bounce and turn forÂ Axar PatelÂ there. He bowls it close to the rough outside off. There is another explosion on the pitch. Leach looks to defend but the ball turns in sharply and catches the inside edge of the bat. It flies to leg slip. Rohit Sharma there takes a sharp catch.
Flighted on middle and leg, Dan milks it wide of long on and keeps the strike.
Floated outside off, Root comes down the track to block it but gets hit on the pad.
The skipper is off the mark! On the pads, Root flicks it with the spin to the leg side and gets a single.

Appeal for a catch but the umpire is unmoved and neither are the Indian players. Another massive turn ofÂ the explosion on the pitch. It is pitched outside off, Lawrence looks to flick but misses. The ball lobs to Pujara at leg slip. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire. Pujara too feels there is no bat involved and Kohli does not take the review. Replay, later on, shows that to be a good call as the ball lobbed off the pad.
This time Lawrence manages to block it calmly.
Ouch! Floated on middle, Lawrence sweeps and hits Shubman GillÂ on the forearm at short leg.

NOT OUT! Root survives a major scare, just by a whisker. Umpire's call on impact and Root will live to fight another day. Flattish delivery on off, Root looks to defend off his back foot but the ball goes between bat and pad and to the keeper. Pant goes up in a confident appeal. The umpire is unmoved though. There is a panel discussion amongst the Indian players. Kohli at the eleventh hour decides to take the review. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge first shows that there is no bat involved. Time for the Ball Tracker now. It looks plumb but the technology shows that the impact is Umpire's call. Kohli is not happy and he is having a chat with the umpire. Root though has a smile on his face. India do not lose the review while for the tourists, their skipper survives!
Floated around off, Root looks to defend but misses as it spins in and hits him high on the pad.
Quicker one on middle, Root looks to work it on the leg side but is late in doing so. It goes off the inner half.
Beats him this time. Lovely from Axar. Floated full and around off, it lands on the rough and beats the outside edge.
Flat and around middle and leg, clipped on the leg side for nothing.
Shortish and around off, Root stays back and punches it through the covers for a single. With this it is STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Starts with a good length delivery down the leg side, Root tries to flick but misses. Siraj got his first Test wicket on home soil by bowling this exact delivery. No luck this time.
Angling into the batsman, on a length around off and staying a touch low, Root is right behind the line in defense.
Digs in a short ball on off, Root pulls it down to long leg and jogs across to the other end for a run.
Beaten! Lovely delivery, keeps the shine of the ball towards covers and gets it to move away from a length outside off, Lawrence is flat-footed as he pushes at it and misses.
A touch short and around off, Dan taps it down safely to covers.
First runs of the morning for Lawrence. Full and around off, Dan gets half-forward and pushes at it with soft hands. It rolls through backward point for a brace.
Starts with a flighted ball around off, it lands and turns away a bit to beat Root's defensive bat.
Again beaten! Unplayable. Axar just lands it full and close to off, Root is forward to play the line but it spins past his bat.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Slightly short and on off, Root moves back and works it behind square leg for a run.
Floated and full on off, Lawrence gets forward and defends it to the leg side.
Probably an arm ball on off, Dan stays back and defends it to the off side. 1 run from the 2nd over of Day 4.
Hurls across a good length delivery in the channel outside off, holding its line, Root covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Good length ball on middle and off, Root blocks it back from the crease. Siraj needs to keep it in the line of the stumps with the pitch offering variable bounce.

And here is the variable bounce... It shoots up from a length close to off, Root sticks back to defend and is taken by surprise. It climbs and kisses the shoulder of his bat as Joe removes the bottom hand.
Around off on a length,Â the batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Full in length and sliding down the leg side, Root tries his best to flick it but it's too wide away from his bat.
Lands it on a good length around off, angling in, Root presents a straight bat in defense.
Flighted and full around off, Lawrence tries to drive it through covers but ends up slicing it through cover-point for two.
Beaten! This will keep happening all day! Tossed up ball around off, Dan is forward in defense but it spins past the outside edge.
Flatter and shorter on middle, it's turned in the gap at mid-wicket for a single.
Unplayable! You cannot play those deliveries. Flatter and around off, at 95 kph and turning away, Root goes back to defend but is beaten.
Swing and a miss! Full and floated outside off, Root goes down to sweep but misses as the ball once again spins past his bat.
Quicker and flatter on middle, Joe moves back and nudges it behind square leg for a run. Retains strike.
Good length ball angling into the batsman, Root defends it from the back foot.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
A length ball around off, angling in, Root has his head down as he pushes it defensively back to the bowler. Siraj fails to collect and there is no mid on. They cross for a single.

Shout for an lbw! Not given. Fuller in length and on off, some movement back into the batsman, Lawrence tries to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The bowler is aware of that and hence no DRS is taken.
Straighter in line and Dan works it through square leg for a run.
Use of the wrists by Root this time as he works a fuller length ball behind square leg for a run. So far so good for England this morning.
Loopy and full around off, Root is forward as he jams it out to the off side.
Flatter and a bit shorter on off, Root goes back and helps it in front of square leg for a run.
Floated and full on off, Dan is on the front foot as he defends it watchfully.
Flatter and fuller on off, Dan is once again on the front foot in defense. Looking quite assured, Lawrence.
Smart bowling! Axar senses the charge from the batsman and fires in a flatter delivery on middle, Lawrence almost gets into a tangle but eventually does well to block it.

Aerial but safe! Patel slows it up in the air and lands it full on off, Lawrence shapes up for a shot across the line but ends up chipping it towards mid off. Doesn't carry to the fielder and they cross for a single.

OUT! Stumped! What was that from Lawrence? Someone would have told him to be positive against the spinners and use his footwork but he has overdone that. And take a moment to praise the glovework of Rishabh Pant. What a superb take by him! Ashwin begins with a flighted ball around leg, probably sensing the charge from the batsman. Lawrence jumps down the track, almost instinctively. But he fails to keep it out and the ball goes through his legs. Pant stays aware of it and does well to grab the ball first and then he stretches out to break the stumps. Dan is out of his crease and will have to depart. 6 wickets more needed for India!
Slower through the air and around off, Stokes is on the back foot in defense.
Stays back again and defends it out on the leg side.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.

Oohhh... how to play those? Full and around off, Stokes tries to defend the line but it spins away viciously with extra bounce and beats his bat. Pant also has no chance of collecting it and the batsmen collect two byes. Rahane with a sliding stop in the deep, good effort.
A slider on the shorter side around off, Ben goes back and plays it down in front of square on the off side. End of a successful over!
Loopy and full outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Flatter and shorter on off, it's fired in, Root goes on the back foot in defense.
Loopy and full on off, Root sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Turning down the leg side, Stokes offers no shot and takes it on his pads.
Uses the spin this time and sweeps a full ball down to deep backward square leg for a run.

FOUR! This is in the range of Root. Too full and around off, Root goes down and sweeps it sweetly well in front of square leg. The mid-wicket fielder runs across to his left but has no chance of cutting it off.
In the air... SAFE! Flighted and full around middle, Stokes tries to sweep but it takes the top edge and falls wide of short fine leg. A run is taken.
Doing well, Joe! Fetches a full ball from outside off and sweeps it to deep square leg for a run.
Flatter and full on off, Stokes walks forward slightly and then brings his bat and pad together in defense.
Floated and full on middle, Stokes defends it by stretching forward.
Unplayable delivery! Full and on middle, spinning away, Stokes tries to defend but it spins away to beat the outside edge.
Ashwin puts it on a fuller length close to off, Stokes draws forward with an angled bat and pushes it out to the off side.
Fuller and on off, Root defends it near his front pad.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
A touch short and flat on off, Root goes back to defend and it takes the inside edge and rolls near his pads.
Quicker ball, on middle, Joe stays back and eases it through square leg for a single.
Floated and full on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Stokes sweeps it with the spin to deep backward square leg for one.
Flatter and shorter on off, Stokes goes on the back foot and punches it to silly point. It deflects back to the bowler.
Strides forward to a full ball and defends it from the outer half of his bat.
Loopy and full around leg, Stokes defends it at the last moment, in front of his pads.
Appeal for an lbw! Flighted and full, Stokes fails to sweep and is pinged on the pads. They appeal but to no avail. Probably pitching outside leg.
Fuller on middle, Stokes reverse sweeps it to backward point where Ishant makes a tumbling stop. They cross for a run.
Risky shot! Full and floated around leg, Root tries to play the paddle sweep but fails to middle it properly. It goes aerially but lands safely behind square leg.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Stokes defends it back.

Flatter and shorter, turning down, Stokes tries to flick but fails to connect properly. There seems to be a slight edge as it quickly goes past Pant. They cross and it's given as runs. Maybe, some gloves, if not an inside edge.
Fuller and on leg, Stokes sweeps it down to fine leg for a run.
Flatter arm ball on off, staying low, Root goes on the back foot and blocks it down.
Once again Root chooses to play from the back foot and defends it back to the right of Patel.
Turn and bounce outside off, Root controls it well and steers it down towards backward point.

SAFE! Loopy and full around off, Stokes pushes it off his front foot to covers and Root is out of his crease in search of a run. Ben sends him back as Axar scores a direct hit at the bowler's end. The third umpire is referred and the replays find Root's bat grounded before the stumps are broken.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Looks to defendÂ it off the front foot but it spins away with extra bounce to beat the outside edge.
Flatter on the pads, helped out to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Stokes drives it off the toe end to mid off.
Flatter and shorter on off, it's blocked off the back foot.
FOUR! Superb shot! Tossed up ball on middle, Root goes down on one knee and sweeps it behind square leg for a boundary.
Beauty! Fuller and closer to off, Root is forward in defense but it spins past his blade.
Flighted and on off, Root tries to defend but there is extra bounce and it goes off the outer edge to point. Played it nice and late.
Fullish and on off, Joe sweeps it in front of square leg for a run.
The broom is out again! Full and around leg, Stokes sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Quicker and fuller on off, Root gets forward and defends it from the outside edge. Soft hands and hence it goes wide of second slip and dies down too.
Loopy and full around leg, Stokes defends it by opening his stance slightly.
Switches to 'round the wickets and delivers a full ball on off, Stokes tries to defend with a straight bat but it spins past it.
Back over the stumps! Flatter and shorter on middle, Stokes defends it from the back foot.
Quicker and flatter outside off, Stokes swings and misses.
Flatter again, on leg, Stokes fails to flick and it goes off his pads to the on side.
Spin and bounce from outside off, Stokes allows it through to Pant.
Starts his spell with a fuller length ball on off, some shape on this one, Root pushes it by getting across towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller in length and close to off, some movement back into the batsman, Root leans forward and defends it from the inside half of his blade.
Pitches it up and on off, Root defends it back to the bowler.
Good lines from Ishant. He is getting some reverse going and is just putting it on and around off. The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fullish and on off, Root flicks it across the line but finds Pujara at mid-wicket who immediately has a shy at the striker's end. Misses the stumps but Rahane is there at gully to back-up the thorow.
Full delivery on off, angling in and straightening a touch from there, Root defends it with gentle hands to the off side. Maiden!
Flighted and full, landing outside leg, Stokes pads it away.
Loopy and full, around middle, Ben presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Whoa! Tossed up ball landing around leg and spinning away with extra bounce outside off, Stokes leaves and Pant collects it in front of his face.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Spinning away from around off, Stokes allows it through.
A carrom ball! Full and around off, spinning in, Stokes is forward and defends it well in the end.
Too full in length around off, Root brings his bat to defend but it takes the inner half and rolls behind square leg for a run.
It's a left-hander in front so Ishant switches to 'round the wickets. Angles in a full ball on off, Stokes defends it to the off side.
Wrong line! It's drifting down the leg side, on a good length, Stokes allows it through.
Very full in length and on off, Stokes jams it out back to the bowler.
Keeps it very full and close to off, shaping back in, Ben defends it out on the off side.
Spears it in on middle, very full again at 134.3 kph, Stokes is watchful as he defends it back.
Flighted and full ball on middle, Root flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Shortish and on off, Stokes goes back to punch and it hits the silly point fielder on the bounce.
Flatter and shorter on off, Stokes hangs back and punches it towards silly point. A half stop again.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Sliding down the leg side, Stokes works it off his pads to square leg.

OUT! Ashwin gets his bunny! 10th time he has dismissed Stokes in Test cricket. A tossed up ball landing full on middle, Stokes leans forward to defend but it takes the inside edge, brushes his pads and lobs behind where Kohli does well to catch it by stretching to his right from second slip. The fight is over from Stokes, he looks down in disappointment and then drags his body to the pavilion. A big blow to England. Five down, five more to go as far as India are concerned.
A length ball on off, staying low, Root does well to defend it out.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On a length and outside off, shaping away, Root pushes at it and misses. Pant collects it on one bounce.
Very full and on off, Root tries to flick but it takes the outer half of his bat and rolls slowly to mid on.
On a driving length and outside off, Root shoulders arms.
Fuller length ball on middle and leg, shaping down, Root fails to flick and it goes off his pads to fine leg for a leg bye.
FOUR! Fine shot! Floated and full around middle and off, Root brings out the reverse-broom, and nails his sweep through point for a boundary.
Tries to play the conventional sweep but hits it on one bounce to leg gully. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Joe initially thinks about a run but it's not available.
Fuller on off, Root reverse sweeps it straight to short third man.
A touch short and on off, Root goes back and pushes it gently to the right of short third man for a run.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Tossed up ball outside off, Pope defends it in the gap at covers and rushes across to the other end to open his account with a single.
FOUR! Not entirely in control of the shot! Full and outside off, Pope gets on the front foot and drives it off the outer portion of his bat through backward point for a boundary.
Angles in a length ball close to off, Pope does well to defend it to the off side.
Pitches it up and around off, Pope pushes it with an angled bat and places it in the gap at deep point for two.
Fuller and on off, Ollie pushes it off his front foot to covers.
Good fielding, Pujara! Very full in length and around leg, Pope flicks it firmly at square leg where Pujara dives to stop the racing ball.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Pope defends it towards covers to end the over. 6 runs from the over, although runs don't matter in this Test match anymore.
Too full in length and around leg, Root sweeps it down to long leg for a run.
Pope brings out the reverse sweep and places it through cover-point. Pujara chases and Ollie gets a couple of runs.
Some extra bounce! Full and flighted on off, Pope leans forward to defend but it takes his gloves and rolls wide of leg gully.
Loopy and full outside off, Pope leans forward and pushes it to point.
Flatter and on middle at 83.4 kph, Pope defends it from the back foot.
Premeditated sweep shot! Pope fetches it from outside off and sends it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Flatter and a bit short on leg, Pope works it through square leg for a run.
Appeal for an lbw! Full and flighted around off, Root tries to reverse sweep but misses. He is hit on the pads but it's spinning down too much.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Dead ball! Spinning down the leg side, Root offers no shot and it scoots past the keeper to the fine leg fence. No shot offered, so nothing added to the scorecard.
Taps it down to point for a single.
Short and on middle, Pope turns and pulls it through square leg for a run.
Almost a return catch! Full and floated on middle, Pope tries to flick but gets a soft leading edge back to the bowler.
Arm ball on off, Pope goes deep inside the crease and pushes it out to covers.
Full and around middle, Pope defends it off the inner half to short fine leg.
Beaten all ends up! Loopy and full on middle, Pope tries to defend but it goes closely past the outside edge.

OUT! Pope holes out! Axar has three and England are six down. The inexperience of Ollie on display here. Floated and full ball around off, Pope opts for the sweep shot ignoring the fact that there is a square leg in place for that shot in the deep. He needed to keep his shot down even if he wants to play it but fails to do so. The ball goes aerially and it's a simple catch for Ishant Sharma. Pope is known to be a good batsman against spinners and this surely will disappoint everyone in the dressing room. More application was needed from him in this battle for survival.
Flatter and shorter on middle, Root goes back and helps it in the gap at mid-wicket for one.
Loopy and full on off, Root reverse sweeps it to point.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Floated and full around off, Root flicks it with the spin to the leg side.
Shout for an lbw! Not given. Tossed up ball on middle, Root tries to reverse sweep but misses. They appeal but to no use. Turning down, maybe.
That is pulled away, through the square leg, for a single.
Flighted and full around off, Foakes is on the front foot as he defends it solidly.
Fuller and on off, Root stretches forward in defense.
Gets on the back foot and turns it through square leg for a run.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Beaten! Foakes leans forward to defend but it spins past his bat.
Once again Foakes is on the front leg, pressing forward to defend but it spins away to take the outer half and lands in front of silly point.
Tossed up ball around off,Â that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Floated and full on off, Root defends it off his front foot.

DROPPED! Loopy full and around off, Root top edges his attempted reverse sweep and Siraj drops a sitter at backward point. Lucky escape for the English skipper. Poor Kuldeep, he needs a wicket to get his confidence back.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Turning down the leg side, Root goes back and allows it through to the keeper.
Too full in length on middle, Root knocks it down to long on for a run.
A nicely flighted delivery, landing full and wide outside off, Foakes reaches out and drives it through extra cover for a couple of runs.
Huge shout for an lbw! Arm ball around middle, skidding down, Root gets back to keep it out but misses. They appeal but it appeared to be missing leg.
BEATEN! Floated outside off, Root looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
Outside off, Root offers no shot to this one.
Flighted delivery on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
On middle, Root keeps it out.
Floated ball outside off, Root looks to sweep but misses it due to the sharp turn on this one.
Spinning down the leg side, Foakes moves back and helps it to square leg.
Leans forward to a full ball and flicks it to short mid-wicket.

OUT! KULDEEP HAS A WICKET! He jumps in joy as Axar catches the ball. Another English batsman known to play spin well departs while attempting a sweep shot. Poor, very poor! A tossed up ball landing full around off, Foakes stretches forward and is way too early into his sweep shot. As a result, it takes the toe end of his bat and balloons straight to Axar Patel standing in front of square leg. He is not going to drop those. England slip further and with that, IT'S LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Floated and full delivery, just outside off, Moeen allows it through to the keeper.
Kuldeep repeats the last delivery but this time from middle and off, Moeen is forced to defend it off his front foot.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Beautiful delivery. Full and flighted on around leg, turning away, Moeen is forward to defend but it spins extra and bounces too to take the outside edge. It flies over Rohit Sharma at second slip who jumps but to no avail. Moeen survives a scare!
Beaten! Lovely full ball on off, Root is forward in defense but it spins past his blade.

OUT! Root falls and the end is nigh for England! Superb delivery. It lands full around off, a puff of dust comes off as it lands and spins away with extra bounce. Root once again is on the front foot to defend but it catches the gloves and goes straight into the hands of Rahane at first slip. All over! Unplayable delivery. You need the luck to survive!
Flatter and outside off, Stone tries to defend but misses.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Short in length on off, Stone punches it from the back foot to cover-point.
A wicket maiden! Tossed up ball on middle, Stone defends it to short mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Short delivery outside off, Moeen looks to cut but misses it due to the away turn on this one.
Googly just outside off, Moeen looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
SIX! Superb shot! Loopy delivery on middle, Ali comes down the track and lofts it over long on for a maximum.
Floated delivery on off, Ali blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up ball outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Short delivery outside off, turning away, Ali punches it through covers for a boundary.

OUT! A flatter delivery, landing full around off and straightening from there, Stone kneels down to play the sweep shot but it goes under his bat and strikes him on the back thigh. They appeal and the finger goes up. Olly takes the DRS. Ultra Edge finds no edge. The Ball Tracker shows that the impact is with umpire's call and it's hitting the stumps. Stone walks back. A fifer on Test debut for Axar and he is ecstatic!
A tossed up ball on middle, spinning down, Broad tries to spin but fails to middle it well.
Uses the spin and works it to square leg for a run.
SIX! Up, up and away! Full and flighted on off, spinning in, Moeen sends it flying over long on for a biggie.
SIX! Dismissed again! Tossed up ball on off, Ali shows his muscle power and dismisses it over long on again. Sending a reminder for the auction, it seems!
SIX! Hat-trick of sixes from Moeen! Advances down the track to a delivery outside off and then launches it with the spin over the bowler's head.
FOUR! Boundaries are flowing all of a sudden! Tossed up ball landing full around off, Broad drives it with the spin to the cover fence.
Beaten! Loopy and full, close to off, Broad tries to sweep but it spins away to beat his bat.
A googly, slightly short and on off, Broad goes on the back foot and defends.
Tries to sweep but misses! Tossed up ball landing full outside leg, Broad fails to sweep.
Too full in length on off, Broad pushes it firmly to short cover.
Quicker through the air, full and on off, Broad defends it off the inner half to square leg. There is a run on offer but Moeen denies it.
Floated full and on middle, Moeen defends it back.
FOUR! Up and over! Flighted and on off, Moeen shimmies down the track and powers it over mid off. Siraj runs back to attempt for the catch but it falls away from him and finds the fence.

SIX! Moeen is playing an entertaining knock! He is showing that if you opt for the attacking intent, you can bat on any pitches in the world. Goes down and smokes a full ball over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Goes down on one knee and sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted and on middle, Broad defends it off the inside half. It lobs in the air but falls safely as there is no short leg present.
Muted appeal for a bat-pad! Not given! Broad tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to silly point.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Flighted and full around off, Moeen makes room, dances down the track and drills his drive to the cover fence.

OUT! Moeen is stumped! End of his entertaining knock and INDIA WIN BY 317 RUNS! Kuldeep shows the heart to flight yet another delivery and lands it wide outside off, Moeen is down the track for another big shot but this time the ball spins past his bat and Rishabh Pant does the rest.
